28/* In order for the format checking to accept the C++ front end
29 diagnostic framework extensions, you must include this file before
30 diagnostic-core.h, not after. We override the definition of GCC_DIAG_STYLE
31 in c-common.h. */
32#undef GCC_DIAG_STYLE
33#define GCC_DIAG_STYLE __gcc_cxxdiag__
34#if defined(GCC_DIAGNOSTIC_CORE_H) || defined (GCC_C_COMMON_H)
35#error \
36In order for the format checking to accept the C++ front end diagnostic \
37framework extensions, you must include this file before diagnostic-core.h and \
38c-common.h, not after.
39#endif

43/* A tree node, together with a location, so that we can track locations
44 (and ranges) during parsing.
45
46 The location is redundant for node kinds that have locations,
47 but not all node kinds do (e.g. constants, and references to
48 params, locals, etc), so we stash a copy here. */
49
50class cp_expr
51{
52public:
53 cp_expr () :
54 m_value (NULL), m_loc (UNKNOWN_LOCATION) {}
55
56 cp_expr (tree value) :
57 m_value (value), m_loc (EXPR_LOCATION (m_value)) {}
58
59 cp_expr (tree value, location_t loc):
60 m_value (value), m_loc (loc) {}
61
62 cp_expr (const cp_expr &other) :
63 m_value (other.m_value), m_loc (other.m_loc) {}
64
65 /* Implicit conversions to tree. */
66 operator tree () const { return m_value; }
67 tree & operator* () { return m_value; }
68 tree & operator-> () { return m_value; }
69
70 tree get_value () const { return m_value; }
71 location_t get_location () const { return m_loc; }
72 location_t get_start () const
73 {
74 source_range src_range = get_range_from_loc (line_table, m_loc);
75 return src_range.m_start;
76 }
77 location_t get_finish () const
78 {
79 source_range src_range = get_range_from_loc (line_table, m_loc);
80 return src_range.m_finish;
81 }
82
83 void set_location (location_t loc)
84 {
85 protected_set_expr_location (m_value, loc);
86 m_loc = loc;
87 }
88
89 void set_range (location_t start, location_t finish)
90 {
91 set_location (make_location (m_loc, start, finish));
92 }
93
94 private:
95 tree m_value;
96 location_t m_loc;
97};
98
99inline bool
100operator == (const cp_expr &lhs, tree rhs)
101{
102 return lhs.get_value () == rhs;
103}

107/* Usage of TREE_LANG_FLAG_?:
108 0: IDENTIFIER_MARKED (IDENTIFIER_NODEs)
109 NEW_EXPR_USE_GLOBAL (in NEW_EXPR).
110 COND_EXPR_IS_VEC_DELETE (in COND_EXPR).
111 DELETE_EXPR_USE_GLOBAL (in DELETE_EXPR).
112 COMPOUND_EXPR_OVERLOADED (in COMPOUND_EXPR).
113 CLEANUP_P (in TRY_BLOCK)
114 AGGR_INIT_VIA_CTOR_P (in AGGR_INIT_EXPR)
115 PTRMEM_OK_P (in ADDR_EXPR, OFFSET_REF, SCOPE_REF)
116 PAREN_STRING_LITERAL (in STRING_CST)
117 CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (in VAR_DECL)
118 KOENIG_LOOKUP_P (in CALL_EXPR)
119 STATEMENT_LIST_NO_SCOPE (in STATEMENT_LIST).
120 EXPR_STMT_STMT_EXPR_RESULT (in EXPR_STMT)
121 STMT_EXPR_NO_SCOPE (in STMT_EXPR)
122 BIND_EXPR_TRY_BLOCK (in BIND_EXPR)
123 TYPENAME_IS_ENUM_P (in TYPENAME_TYPE)
124 OMP_FOR_GIMPLIFYING_P (in OMP_FOR, OMP_SIMD, OMP_DISTRIBUTE,
125 and OMP_TASKLOOP)
126 BASELINK_QUALIFIED_P (in BASELINK)
127 TARGET_EXPR_IMPLICIT_P (in TARGET_EXPR)
128 TEMPLATE_PARM_PARAMETER_PACK (in TEMPLATE_PARM_INDEX)
129 TREE_INDIRECT_USING (in a TREE_LIST of using-directives)
130 ATTR_IS_DEPENDENT (in the TREE_LIST for an attribute)
131 ABI_TAG_IMPLICIT (in the TREE_LIST for the argument of abi_tag)
132 CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (in CONSTRUCTOR)
133 LAMBDA_EXPR_CAPTURES_THIS_P (in LAMBDA_EXPR)
134 DECLTYPE_FOR_LAMBDA_CAPTURE (in DECLTYPE_TYPE)
135 VEC_INIT_EXPR_IS_CONSTEXPR (in VEC_INIT_EXPR)
136 DECL_OVERRIDE_P (in FUNCTION_DECL)
137 IMPLICIT_CONV_EXPR_DIRECT_INIT (in IMPLICIT_CONV_EXPR)
138 TRANSACTION_EXPR_IS_STMT (in TRANSACTION_EXPR)
139 CONVERT_EXPR_VBASE_PATH (in CONVERT_EXPR)
140 OVL_ARG_DEPENDENT (in OVERLOAD)
141 PACK_EXPANSION_LOCAL_P (in *_PACK_EXPANSION)
142 TINFO_HAS_ACCESS_ERRORS (in TEMPLATE_INFO)
143 SIZEOF_EXPR_TYPE_P (in SIZEOF_EXPR)
144 COMPOUND_REQ_NOEXCEPT_P (in COMPOUND_REQ)
145 WILDCARD_PACK_P (in WILDCARD_DECL)
146 BLOCK_OUTER_CURLY_BRACE_P (in BLOCK)
147 FOLD_EXPR_MODOP_P (*_FOLD_EXPR)
148 IF_STMT_CONSTEXPR_P (IF_STMT)
149 TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM_FOR_CLASS (TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM)
150 1: IDENTIFIER_VIRTUAL_P (in IDENTIFIER_NODE)
151 TI_PENDING_TEMPLATE_FLAG.
152 TEMPLATE_PARMS_FOR_INLINE.
153 DELETE_EXPR_USE_VEC (in DELETE_EXPR).
154 (TREE_CALLS_NEW) (in _EXPR or _REF) (commented-out).
155 ICS_ELLIPSIS_FLAG (in _CONV)
156 DECL_INITIALIZED_P (in VAR_DECL)
157 TYPENAME_IS_CLASS_P (in TYPENAME_TYPE)
158 STMT_IS_FULL_EXPR_P (in _STMT)
159 TARGET_EXPR_LIST_INIT_P (in TARGET_EXPR)
160 LAMBDA_EXPR_MUTABLE_P (in LAMBDA_EXPR)
161 DECL_FINAL_P (in FUNCTION_DECL)
162 QUALIFIED_NAME_IS_TEMPLATE (in SCOPE_REF)
163 DECLTYPE_FOR_INIT_CAPTURE (in DECLTYPE_TYPE)
164 CONSTRUCTOR_NO_IMPLICIT_ZERO (in CONSTRUCTOR)
165 TINFO_USED_TEMPLATE_ID (in TEMPLATE_INFO)
166 PACK_EXPANSION_SIZEOF_P (in *_PACK_EXPANSION)
167 2: IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (in IDENTIFIER_NODE)
168 ICS_THIS_FLAG (in _CONV)
169 DECL_INITIALIZED_BY_CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_P (in VAR_DECL)
170 STATEMENT_LIST_TRY_BLOCK (in STATEMENT_LIST)
171 TYPENAME_IS_RESOLVING_P (in TYPE_NAME_TYPE)
172 TARGET_EXPR_DIRECT_INIT_P (in TARGET_EXPR)
173 FNDECL_USED_AUTO (in FUNCTION_DECL)
174 DECLTYPE_FOR_LAMBDA_PROXY (in DECLTYPE_TYPE)
175 REF_PARENTHESIZED_P (in COMPONENT_REF, INDIRECT_REF, SCOPE_REF)
176 AGGR_INIT_ZERO_FIRST (in AGGR_INIT_EXPR)
177 CONSTRUCTOR_MUTABLE_POISON (in CONSTRUCTOR)
178 3: (TREE_REFERENCE_EXPR) (in NON_LVALUE_EXPR) (commented-out).
179 ICS_BAD_FLAG (in _CONV)
180 FN_TRY_BLOCK_P (in TRY_BLOCK)
181 IDENTIFIER_CTOR_OR_DTOR_P (in IDENTIFIER_NODE)
182 BIND_EXPR_BODY_BLOCK (in BIND_EXPR)
183 DECL_NON_TRIVIALLY_INITIALIZED_P (in VAR_DECL)
184 CALL_EXPR_ORDERED_ARGS (in CALL_EXPR, AGGR_INIT_EXPR)
185 DECLTYPE_FOR_REF_CAPTURE (in DECLTYPE_TYPE)
186 4: TREE_HAS_CONSTRUCTOR (in INDIRECT_REF, SAVE_EXPR, CONSTRUCTOR,
187 CALL_EXPR, or FIELD_DECL).
188 IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P (in IDENTIFIER_NODE)
189 DECL_TINFO_P (in VAR_DECL)
190 FUNCTION_REF_QUALIFIED (in FUNCTION_TYPE, METHOD_TYPE)
191 5: C_IS_RESERVED_WORD (in IDENTIFIER_NODE)
192 DECL_VTABLE_OR_VTT_P (in VAR_DECL)
193 FUNCTION_RVALUE_QUALIFIED (in FUNCTION_TYPE, METHOD_TYPE)
194 CALL_EXPR_REVERSE_ARGS (in CALL_EXPR, AGGR_INIT_EXPR)
195 6: IDENTIFIER_REPO_CHOSEN (in IDENTIFIER_NODE)
196 DECL_CONSTRUCTION_VTABLE_P (in VAR_DECL)
197 TYPE_MARKED_P (in _TYPE)
198 RANGE_FOR_IVDEP (in RANGE_FOR_STMT)
199 CALL_EXPR_OPERATOR_SYNTAX (in CALL_EXPR, AGGR_INIT_EXPR)
200
201 Usage of TYPE_LANG_FLAG_?:
202 0: TYPE_DEPENDENT_P
203 1: TYPE_HAS_USER_CONSTRUCTOR.
204 2: TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (in FUNCTION_TYPE, METHOD_TYPE)
205 TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FLAG (in RECORD_TYPE)
206 4: TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR
207 5: CLASS_TYPE_P (in RECORD_TYPE and UNION_TYPE)
208 ENUM_FIXED_UNDERLYING_TYPE_P (in ENUMERAL_TYPE)
209 AUTO_IS_DECLTYPE (in TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM)
210 REFERENCE_VLA_OK (in REFERENCE_TYPE)
211 6: TYPE_DEPENDENT_P_VALID
212
213 Usage of DECL_LANG_FLAG_?:
214 0: DECL_ERROR_REPORTED (in VAR_DECL).
215 DECL_TEMPLATE_PARM_P (in PARM_DECL, CONST_DECL, TYPE_DECL, or TEMPLATE_DECL)
216 DECL_LOCAL_FUNCTION_P (in FUNCTION_DECL)
217 DECL_MUTABLE_P (in FIELD_DECL)
218 DECL_DEPENDENT_P (in USING_DECL)
219 LABEL_DECL_BREAK (in LABEL_DECL)
220 1: C_TYPEDEF_EXPLICITLY_SIGNED (in TYPE_DECL).
221 DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATED (in a VAR_DECL or a FUNCTION_DECL)
222 DECL_MEMBER_TEMPLATE_P (in TEMPLATE_DECL)
223 USING_DECL_TYPENAME_P (in USING_DECL)
224 DECL_VLA_CAPTURE_P (in FIELD_DECL)
225 DECL_ARRAY_PARAMETER_P (in PARM_DECL)
226 LABEL_DECL_CONTINUE (in LABEL_DECL)
227 2: DECL_THIS_EXTERN (in VAR_DECL or FUNCTION_DECL).
228 DECL_IMPLICIT_TYPEDEF_P (in a TYPE_DECL)
229 DECL_CONSTRAINT_VAR_P (in a PARM_DECL)
230 TEMPLATE_DECL_COMPLEX_ALIAS_P (in TEMPLATE_DECL)
231 DECL_INSTANTIATING_NSDMI_P (in a FIELD_DECL)
232 3: DECL_IN_AGGR_P.
233 4: DECL_C_BIT_FIELD (in a FIELD_DECL)
234 DECL_ANON_UNION_VAR_P (in a VAR_DECL)
235 DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P (in a TYPE_DECL)
236 DECL_INVALID_OVERRIDER_P (in a FUNCTION_DECL)
237 5: DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN.
238 6: DECL_THIS_STATIC (in VAR_DECL or FUNCTION_DECL).
239 DECL_FIELD_IS_BASE (in FIELD_DECL)
240 TYPE_DECL_ALIAS_P (in TYPE_DECL)
241 7: DECL_DEAD_FOR_LOCAL (in VAR_DECL).
242 DECL_THUNK_P (in a member FUNCTION_DECL)
243 DECL_NORMAL_CAPTURE_P (in FIELD_DECL)
244 8: DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (in VAR_DECL, FUNCTION_DECL)
245
246 Usage of language-independent fields in a language-dependent manner:
247
248 TYPE_ALIAS_SET
249 This field is used by TYPENAME_TYPEs, TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARMs, and so
250 forth as a substitute for the mark bits provided in `lang_type'.
251 At present, only the six low-order bits are used.
252
253 TYPE_LANG_SLOT_1
254 For an ENUMERAL_TYPE, this is ENUM_TEMPLATE_INFO.
255 For a FUNCTION_TYPE or METHOD_TYPE, this is TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS
256
257 BINFO_VIRTUALS
258 For a binfo, this is a TREE_LIST. There is an entry for each
259 virtual function declared either in BINFO or its direct and
260 indirect primary bases.
261
262 The BV_DELTA of each node gives the amount by which to adjust the
263 `this' pointer when calling the function. If the method is an
264 overridden version of a base class method, then it is assumed
265 that, prior to adjustment, the this pointer points to an object
266 of the base class.
267
268 The BV_VCALL_INDEX of each node, if non-NULL, gives the vtable
269 index of the vcall offset for this entry.
270
271 The BV_FN is the declaration for the virtual function itself.
272
273 If BV_LOST_PRIMARY is set, it means that this entry is for a lost
274 primary virtual base and can be left null in the vtable.
275
276 BINFO_VTABLE
277 This is an expression with POINTER_TYPE that gives the value
278 to which the vptr should be initialized. Use get_vtbl_decl_for_binfo
279 to extract the VAR_DECL for the complete vtable.
280
281 DECL_VINDEX
282 This field is NULL for a non-virtual function. For a virtual
283 function, it is eventually set to an INTEGER_CST indicating the
284 index in the vtable at which this function can be found. When
285 a virtual function is declared, but before it is known what
286 function is overridden, this field is the error_mark_node.
287
288 Temporarily, it may be set to a TREE_LIST whose TREE_VALUE is
289 the virtual function this one overrides, and whose TREE_CHAIN is
290 the old DECL_VINDEX. */
291
292/* Language-specific tree checkers. */
293
294#define VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_CHECK(NODE) \
295 TREE_CHECK2(NODE,VAR_DECL,FUNCTION_DECL)
296
297#define TYPE_FUNCTION_OR_TEMPLATE_DECL_CHECK(NODE) \
298 TREE_CHECK3(NODE,TYPE_DECL,TEMPLATE_DECL,FUNCTION_DECL)
299
300#define TYPE_FUNCTION_OR_TEMPLATE_DECL_P(NODE) \
301 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_DECL || TREE_CODE (NODE) == TEMPLATE_DECL \
302 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == FUNCTION_DECL)
303
304#define VAR_FUNCTION_OR_PARM_DECL_CHECK(NODE) \
305 TREE_CHECK3(NODE,VAR_DECL,FUNCTION_DECL,PARM_DECL)
306
307#define VAR_TEMPL_TYPE_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_CHECK(NODE) \
308 TREE_CHECK4(NODE,VAR_DECL,FUNCTION_DECL,TYPE_DECL,TEMPLATE_DECL)
309
310#define VAR_TEMPL_TYPE_FIELD_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_CHECK(NODE) \
311 TREE_CHECK5(NODE,VAR_DECL,FIELD_DECL,FUNCTION_DECL,TYPE_DECL,TEMPLATE_DECL)
312
313#define BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM_TYPE_CHECK(NODE) \
314 TREE_CHECK(NODE,BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM)
315
316#if defined ENABLE_TREE_CHECKING && (GCC_VERSION >= 2007)
317#define THUNK_FUNCTION_CHECK(NODE) __extension__ \
318({ __typeof (NODE) const __t = (NODE); \
319 if (TREE_CODE (__t) != FUNCTION_DECL || !__t->decl_common.lang_specific \
320 || !__t->decl_common.lang_specific->u.fn.thunk_p) \
321 tree_check_failed (__t, __FILE__, __LINE__, __FUNCTION__, 0); \
322 __t; })
323#else
324#define THUNK_FUNCTION_CHECK(NODE) (NODE)
325#endif

327/* Language-dependent contents of an identifier. */
328
329struct GTY(()) lang_identifier {
330 struct c_common_identifier c_common;
331 cxx_binding *namespace_bindings;
332 cxx_binding *bindings;
333 tree class_template_info;
334 tree label_value;
335};
336
337/* Return a typed pointer version of T if it designates a
338 C++ front-end identifier. */
339inline lang_identifier*
340identifier_p (tree t)
341{
342 if (TREE_CODE (t) == IDENTIFIER_NODE)
343 return (lang_identifier*) t;
344 return NULL;
345}
346
347/* In an IDENTIFIER_NODE, nonzero if this identifier is actually a
348 keyword. C_RID_CODE (node) is then the RID_* value of the keyword. */
349
350#define C_IS_RESERVED_WORD(ID) TREE_LANG_FLAG_5 (ID)
351
352#define LANG_IDENTIFIER_CAST(NODE) \
353 ((struct lang_identifier*)IDENTIFIER_NODE_CHECK (NODE))
354
355struct GTY(()) template_parm_index {
356 struct tree_common common;
357 int index;
358 int level;
359 int orig_level;
360 tree decl;
361};
362
363struct GTY(()) ptrmem_cst {
364 struct tree_common common;
365 tree member;
366};
367typedef struct ptrmem_cst * ptrmem_cst_t;

369#define IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE(NODE) \
370 namespace_binding ((NODE), global_namespace)
371#define SET_IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE(NODE, VAL) \
372 set_namespace_binding ((NODE), global_namespace, (VAL))
373#define IDENTIFIER_NAMESPACE_VALUE(NODE) \
374 namespace_binding ((NODE), current_namespace)
375#define SET_IDENTIFIER_NAMESPACE_VALUE(NODE, VAL) \
376 set_namespace_binding ((NODE), current_namespace, (VAL))
377
378#define CLEANUP_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (TRY_BLOCK_CHECK (NODE))
379
380#define BIND_EXPR_TRY_BLOCK(NODE) \
381 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (BIND_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
382
383/* Used to mark the block around the member initializers and cleanups. */
384#define BIND_EXPR_BODY_BLOCK(NODE) \
385 TREE_LANG_FLAG_3 (BIND_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
386#define FUNCTION_NEEDS_BODY_BLOCK(NODE) \
387 (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (NODE) || DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
388 || LAMBDA_FUNCTION_P (NODE))
389
390#define STATEMENT_LIST_NO_SCOPE(NODE) \
391 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (STATEMENT_LIST_CHECK (NODE))
392#define STATEMENT_LIST_TRY_BLOCK(NODE) \
393 TREE_LANG_FLAG_2 (STATEMENT_LIST_CHECK (NODE))
394
395/* Mark the outer curly brace BLOCK. */
396#define BLOCK_OUTER_CURLY_BRACE_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (BLOCK_CHECK (NODE))
397
398/* Nonzero if this statement should be considered a full-expression,
399 i.e., if temporaries created during this statement should have
400 their destructors run at the end of this statement. */
401#define STMT_IS_FULL_EXPR_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 ((NODE))
402
403/* Marks the result of a statement expression. */
404#define EXPR_STMT_STMT_EXPR_RESULT(NODE) \
405 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (EXPR_STMT_CHECK (NODE))
406
407/* Nonzero if this statement-expression does not have an associated scope. */
408#define STMT_EXPR_NO_SCOPE(NODE) \
409 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (STMT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
410
411#define COND_EXPR_IS_VEC_DELETE(NODE) \
412 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (COND_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
413
414/* Returns nonzero iff TYPE1 and TYPE2 are the same type, in the usual
415 sense of `same'. */
416#define same_type_p(TYPE1, TYPE2) \
417 comptypes ((TYPE1), (TYPE2), COMPARE_STRICT)
418
419/* Returns nonzero iff NODE is a declaration for the global function
420 `main'. */
421#define DECL_MAIN_P(NODE) \
422 (DECL_EXTERN_C_FUNCTION_P (NODE) \
423 && DECL_NAME (NODE) != NULL_TREE \
424 && MAIN_NAME_P (DECL_NAME (NODE)) \
425 && flag_hosted)
426
427/* The overloaded FUNCTION_DECL. */
428#define OVL_FUNCTION(NODE) \
429 (((struct tree_overload*)OVERLOAD_CHECK (NODE))->function)
430#define OVL_CHAIN(NODE) TREE_CHAIN (NODE)
431/* Polymorphic access to FUNCTION and CHAIN. */
432#define OVL_CURRENT(NODE) \
433 ((TREE_CODE (NODE) == OVERLOAD) ? OVL_FUNCTION (NODE) : (NODE))
434#define OVL_NEXT(NODE) \
435 ((TREE_CODE (NODE) == OVERLOAD) ? TREE_CHAIN (NODE) : NULL_TREE)
436/* If set, this was imported in a using declaration.
437 This is not to confuse with being used somewhere, which
438 is not important for this node. */
439#define OVL_USED(NODE) TREE_USED (OVERLOAD_CHECK (NODE))
440/* If set, this OVERLOAD was created for argument-dependent lookup
441 and can be freed afterward. */
442#define OVL_ARG_DEPENDENT(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (OVERLOAD_CHECK (NODE))
443
444struct GTY(()) tree_overload {
445 struct tree_common common;
446 tree function;
447};
448
449struct GTY(()) tree_template_decl {
450 struct tree_decl_common common;
451 tree arguments;
452 tree result;
453};
454
455/* Returns true iff NODE is a BASELINK. */
456#define BASELINK_P(NODE) \
457 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == BASELINK)
458/* The BINFO indicating the base in which lookup found the
459 BASELINK_FUNCTIONS. */
460#define BASELINK_BINFO(NODE) \
461 (((struct tree_baselink*) BASELINK_CHECK (NODE))->binfo)
462/* The functions referred to by the BASELINK; either a FUNCTION_DECL,
463 a TEMPLATE_DECL, an OVERLOAD, or a TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR. */
464#define BASELINK_FUNCTIONS(NODE) \
465 (((struct tree_baselink*) BASELINK_CHECK (NODE))->functions)
466/* The BINFO in which the search for the functions indicated by this baselink
467 began. This base is used to determine the accessibility of functions
468 selected by overload resolution. */
469#define BASELINK_ACCESS_BINFO(NODE) \
470 (((struct tree_baselink*) BASELINK_CHECK (NODE))->access_binfo)
471/* For a type-conversion operator, the BASELINK_OPTYPE indicates the type
472 to which the conversion should occur. This value is important if
473 the BASELINK_FUNCTIONS include a template conversion operator --
474 the BASELINK_OPTYPE can be used to determine what type the user
475 requested. */
476#define BASELINK_OPTYPE(NODE) \
477 (TREE_CHAIN (BASELINK_CHECK (NODE)))
478/* Nonzero if this baselink was from a qualified lookup. */
479#define BASELINK_QUALIFIED_P(NODE) \
480 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (BASELINK_CHECK (NODE))
481
482struct GTY(()) tree_baselink {
483 struct tree_common common;
484 tree binfo;
485 tree functions;
486 tree access_binfo;
487};

489/* The different kinds of ids that we encounter. */
490
491enum cp_id_kind
492{
493 /* Not an id at all. */
494 CP_ID_KIND_NONE,
495 /* An unqualified-id that is not a template-id. */
496 CP_ID_KIND_UNQUALIFIED,
497 /* An unqualified-id that is a dependent name. */
498 CP_ID_KIND_UNQUALIFIED_DEPENDENT,
499 /* An unqualified template-id. */
500 CP_ID_KIND_TEMPLATE_ID,
501 /* A qualified-id. */
502 CP_ID_KIND_QUALIFIED
503};

506/* The various kinds of C++0x warnings we encounter. */
507
508enum cpp0x_warn_str
509{
510 /* extended initializer lists */
511 CPP0X_INITIALIZER_LISTS,
512 /* explicit conversion operators */
513 CPP0X_EXPLICIT_CONVERSION,
514 /* variadic templates */
515 CPP0X_VARIADIC_TEMPLATES,
516 /* lambda expressions */
517 CPP0X_LAMBDA_EXPR,
518 /* C++0x auto */
519 CPP0X_AUTO,
520 /* scoped enums */
521 CPP0X_SCOPED_ENUMS,
522 /* defaulted and deleted functions */
523 CPP0X_DEFAULTED_DELETED,
524 /* inline namespaces */
525 CPP0X_INLINE_NAMESPACES,
526 /* override controls, override/final */
527 CPP0X_OVERRIDE_CONTROLS,
528 /* non-static data member initializers */
529 CPP0X_NSDMI,
530 /* user defined literals */
531 CPP0X_USER_DEFINED_LITERALS,
532 /* delegating constructors */
533 CPP0X_DELEGATING_CTORS,
534 /* inheriting constructors */
535 CPP0X_INHERITING_CTORS,
536 /* C++11 attributes */
537 CPP0X_ATTRIBUTES,
538 /* ref-qualified member functions */
539 CPP0X_REF_QUALIFIER
540};

542/* The various kinds of operation used by composite_pointer_type. */
543
544enum composite_pointer_operation
545{
546 /* comparison */
547 CPO_COMPARISON,
548 /* conversion */
549 CPO_CONVERSION,
550 /* conditional expression */
551 CPO_CONDITIONAL_EXPR
552};
553
554/* Possible cases of expression list used by build_x_compound_expr_from_list. */
555enum expr_list_kind {
556 ELK_INIT, /* initializer */
557 ELK_MEM_INIT, /* member initializer */
558 ELK_FUNC_CAST /* functional cast */
559};
560
561/* Possible cases of implicit bad rhs conversions. */
562enum impl_conv_rhs {
563 ICR_DEFAULT_ARGUMENT, /* default argument */
564 ICR_CONVERTING, /* converting */
565 ICR_INIT, /* initialization */
566 ICR_ARGPASS, /* argument passing */
567 ICR_RETURN, /* return */
568 ICR_ASSIGN /* assignment */
569};
570
571/* Possible cases of implicit or explicit bad conversions to void. */
572enum impl_conv_void {
573 ICV_CAST, /* (explicit) conversion to void */
574 ICV_SECOND_OF_COND, /* second operand of conditional expression */
575 ICV_THIRD_OF_COND, /* third operand of conditional expression */
576 ICV_RIGHT_OF_COMMA, /* right operand of comma operator */
577 ICV_LEFT_OF_COMMA, /* left operand of comma operator */
578 ICV_STATEMENT, /* statement */
579 ICV_THIRD_IN_FOR /* for increment expression */
580};
581
582/* Possible invalid uses of an abstract class that might not have a
583 specific associated declaration. */
584enum GTY(()) abstract_class_use {
585 ACU_UNKNOWN, /* unknown or decl provided */
586 ACU_CAST, /* cast to abstract class */
587 ACU_NEW, /* new-expression of abstract class */
588 ACU_THROW, /* throw-expression of abstract class */
589 ACU_CATCH, /* catch-parameter of abstract class */
590 ACU_ARRAY, /* array of abstract class */
591 ACU_RETURN, /* return type of abstract class */
592 ACU_PARM /* parameter type of abstract class */
593};

595/* Macros for access to language-specific slots in an identifier. */
596
597#define IDENTIFIER_NAMESPACE_BINDINGS(NODE) \
598 (LANG_IDENTIFIER_CAST (NODE)->namespace_bindings)
599#define IDENTIFIER_TEMPLATE(NODE) \
600 (LANG_IDENTIFIER_CAST (NODE)->class_template_info)
601
602/* The IDENTIFIER_BINDING is the innermost cxx_binding for the
603 identifier. It's PREVIOUS is the next outermost binding. Each
604 VALUE field is a DECL for the associated declaration. Thus,
605 name lookup consists simply of pulling off the node at the front
606 of the list (modulo oddities for looking up the names of types,
607 and such.) You can use SCOPE field to determine the scope
608 that bound the name. */
609#define IDENTIFIER_BINDING(NODE) \
610 (LANG_IDENTIFIER_CAST (NODE)->bindings)
611
612/* TREE_TYPE only indicates on local and class scope the current
613 type. For namespace scope, the presence of a type in any namespace
614 is indicated with global_type_node, and the real type behind must
615 be found through lookup. */
616#define IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE(NODE) identifier_type_value (NODE)
617#define REAL_IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE(NODE) TREE_TYPE (NODE)
618#define SET_IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE(NODE,TYPE) (TREE_TYPE (NODE) = (TYPE))
619#define IDENTIFIER_HAS_TYPE_VALUE(NODE) (IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE (NODE) ? 1 : 0)
620
621#define IDENTIFIER_LABEL_VALUE(NODE) \
622 (LANG_IDENTIFIER_CAST (NODE)->label_value)
623#define SET_IDENTIFIER_LABEL_VALUE(NODE, VALUE) \
624 IDENTIFIER_LABEL_VALUE (NODE) = (VALUE)
625
626/* Nonzero if this identifier is used as a virtual function name somewhere
627 (optimizes searches). */
628#define IDENTIFIER_VIRTUAL_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (NODE)
629
630/* Nonzero if this identifier is the prefix for a mangled C++ operator
631 name. */
632#define IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_2 (NODE)
633
634/* Nonzero if this identifier is the name of a type-conversion
635 operator. */
636#define IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P(NODE) \
637 TREE_LANG_FLAG_4 (NODE)
638
639/* Nonzero if this identifier is the name of a constructor or
640 destructor. */
641#define IDENTIFIER_CTOR_OR_DTOR_P(NODE) \
642 TREE_LANG_FLAG_3 (NODE)
643
644/* True iff NAME is the DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME for an entity with vague
645 linkage which the prelinker has assigned to this translation
646 unit. */
647#define IDENTIFIER_REPO_CHOSEN(NAME) \
648 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_6 (NAME))
649
650/* In a RECORD_TYPE or UNION_TYPE, nonzero if any component is read-only. */
651#define C_TYPE_FIELDS_READONLY(TYPE) \
652 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (TYPE)->fields_readonly)
653
654/* The tokens stored in the default argument. */
655
656#define DEFARG_TOKENS(NODE) \
657 (((struct tree_default_arg *)DEFAULT_ARG_CHECK (NODE))->tokens)
658#define DEFARG_INSTANTIATIONS(NODE) \
659 (((struct tree_default_arg *)DEFAULT_ARG_CHECK (NODE))->instantiations)
660
661struct GTY (()) tree_default_arg {
662 struct tree_common common;
663 struct cp_token_cache *tokens;
664 vec<tree, va_gc> *instantiations;
665};
666
667
668#define DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_PATTERN(NODE) \
669 (((struct tree_deferred_noexcept *)DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_CHECK (NODE))->pattern)
670#define DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_ARGS(NODE) \
671 (((struct tree_deferred_noexcept *)DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_CHECK (NODE))->args)
672#define DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_SPEC_P(NODE) \
673 ((NODE) && (TREE_PURPOSE (NODE)) \
674 && (TREE_CODE (TREE_PURPOSE (NODE)) == DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT))
675#define UNEVALUATED_NOEXCEPT_SPEC_P(NODE) \
676 (DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_SPEC_P (NODE) \
677 && DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_PATTERN (TREE_PURPOSE (NODE)) == NULL_TREE)
678
679struct GTY (()) tree_deferred_noexcept {
680 struct tree_base base;
681 tree pattern;
682 tree args;
683};

685
686/* The condition associated with the static assertion. This must be
687 an integral constant expression. */
688#define STATIC_ASSERT_CONDITION(NODE) \
689 (((struct tree_static_assert *)STATIC_ASSERT_CHECK (NODE))->condition)
690
691/* The message associated with the static assertion. This must be a
692 string constant, which will be emitted as an error message when the
693 static assert condition is false. */
694#define STATIC_ASSERT_MESSAGE(NODE) \
695 (((struct tree_static_assert *)STATIC_ASSERT_CHECK (NODE))->message)
696
697/* Source location information for a static assertion. */
698#define STATIC_ASSERT_SOURCE_LOCATION(NODE) \
699 (((struct tree_static_assert *)STATIC_ASSERT_CHECK (NODE))->location)
700
701struct GTY (()) tree_static_assert {
702 struct tree_common common;
703 tree condition;
704 tree message;
705 location_t location;
706};

709 struct tree_common common;

749/* The types that we are processing. */
750#define TRAIT_EXPR_TYPE1(NODE) \
751 (((struct tree_trait_expr *)TRAIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->type1)
752
753#define TRAIT_EXPR_TYPE2(NODE) \
754 (((struct tree_trait_expr *)TRAIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->type2)
755
756/* The specific trait that we are processing. */
757#define TRAIT_EXPR_KIND(NODE) \
758 (((struct tree_trait_expr *)TRAIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->kind)

766
767/* Based off of TYPE_UNNAMED_P. */
768#define LAMBDA_TYPE_P(NODE) \
769 (CLASS_TYPE_P (NODE) && CLASSTYPE_LAMBDA_EXPR (NODE))
770
771/* Test if FUNCTION_DECL is a lambda function. */
772#define LAMBDA_FUNCTION_P(FNDECL) \
773 (DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (FNDECL) == CALL_EXPR \
774 && LAMBDA_TYPE_P (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (FNDECL)))
775
776enum cp_lambda_default_capture_mode_type {
777 CPLD_NONE,
778 CPLD_COPY,
779 CPLD_REFERENCE
780};
781
782/* The method of default capture, if any. */
783#define LAMBDA_EXPR_DEFAULT_CAPTURE_MODE(NODE) \
784 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->default_capture_mode)
785
786/* The capture-list, including `this'. Each capture is stored as a FIELD_DECL
787 * so that the name, type, and field are all together, whether or not it has
788 * been added to the lambda's class type.
789 TREE_LIST:
790 TREE_PURPOSE: The FIELD_DECL for this capture.
791 TREE_VALUE: The initializer. This is part of a GNU extension. */
792#define LAMBDA_EXPR_CAPTURE_LIST(NODE) \
793 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->capture_list)
794
795/* During parsing of the lambda-introducer, the node in the capture-list
796 that holds the 'this' capture. During parsing of the body, the
797 capture proxy for that node. */
798#define LAMBDA_EXPR_THIS_CAPTURE(NODE) \
799 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->this_capture)
800
801/* Predicate tracking whether `this' is in the effective capture set. */
802#define LAMBDA_EXPR_CAPTURES_THIS_P(NODE) \
803 LAMBDA_EXPR_THIS_CAPTURE(NODE)
804
805/* Predicate tracking whether the lambda was declared 'mutable'. */
806#define LAMBDA_EXPR_MUTABLE_P(NODE) \
807 TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
808
809/* The return type in the expression.
810 * NULL_TREE indicates that none was specified. */
811#define LAMBDA_EXPR_RETURN_TYPE(NODE) \
812 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->return_type)
813
814/* The source location of the lambda. */
815#define LAMBDA_EXPR_LOCATION(NODE) \
816 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->locus)
817
818/* The mangling scope for the lambda: FUNCTION_DECL, PARM_DECL, VAR_DECL,
819 FIELD_DECL or NULL_TREE. If this is NULL_TREE, we have no linkage. */
820#define LAMBDA_EXPR_EXTRA_SCOPE(NODE) \
821 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->extra_scope)
822
823/* If EXTRA_SCOPE, this is the number of the lambda within that scope. */
824#define LAMBDA_EXPR_DISCRIMINATOR(NODE) \
825 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->discriminator)
826
827/* During parsing of the lambda, a vector of capture proxies which need
828 to be pushed once we're done processing a nested lambda. */
829#define LAMBDA_EXPR_PENDING_PROXIES(NODE) \
830 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->pending_proxies)
831
832/* The closure type of the lambda. Note that the TREE_TYPE of a
833 LAMBDA_EXPR is always NULL_TREE, because we need to instantiate the
834 LAMBDA_EXPR in order to instantiate the type. */
835#define LAMBDA_EXPR_CLOSURE(NODE) \
836 (((struct tree_lambda_expr *)LAMBDA_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))->closure)
837
838struct GTY (()) tree_lambda_expr
839{
840 struct tree_typed typed;
841 tree capture_list;
842 tree this_capture;
843 tree return_type;
844 tree extra_scope;
845 tree closure;
846 vec<tree, va_gc> *pending_proxies;
847 location_t locus;
848 enum cp_lambda_default_capture_mode_type default_capture_mode;
849 int discriminator;
850};

852/* A (typedef,context,usage location) triplet.
853 It represents a typedef used through a
854 context at a given source location.
855 e.g.
856 struct foo {
857 typedef int myint;
858 };
859
860 struct bar {
861 foo::myint v; // #1<-- this location.
862 };
863
864 In bar, the triplet will be (myint, foo, #1).
865 */
866struct GTY(()) qualified_typedef_usage_s {
867 tree typedef_decl;
868 tree context;
869 location_t locus;
870};
871typedef struct qualified_typedef_usage_s qualified_typedef_usage_t;
872
873/* Non-zero if this template specialization has access violations that
874 should be rechecked when the function is instantiated outside argument
875 deduction. */
876#define TINFO_HAS_ACCESS_ERRORS(NODE) \
877 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (TEMPLATE_INFO_CHECK (NODE)))
878#define FNDECL_HAS_ACCESS_ERRORS(NODE) \
879 (TINFO_HAS_ACCESS_ERRORS (DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE)))
880
881/* Non-zero if this variable template specialization was specified using a
882 template-id, so it's a partial or full specialization and not a definition
883 of the member template of a particular class specialization. */
884#define TINFO_USED_TEMPLATE_ID(NODE) \
885 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (TEMPLATE_INFO_CHECK (NODE)))
886
887struct GTY(()) tree_template_info {
888 struct tree_common common;
889 vec<qualified_typedef_usage_t, va_gc> *typedefs_needing_access_checking;
890};
891
892// Constraint information for a C++ declaration. Constraint information is
893// comprised of:
894//
895// - a constraint expression introduced by the template header
896// - a constraint expression introduced by a function declarator
897// - the associated constraints, which are the conjunction of those,
898// and used for declaration matching
899//
900// The template and declarator requirements are kept to support pretty
901// printing constrained declarations.
902struct GTY(()) tree_constraint_info {
903 struct tree_base base;
904 tree template_reqs;
905 tree declarator_reqs;
906 tree associated_constr;
907};
908
909// Require that pointer P is non-null before returning.
910template<typename T>
911inline T*
912check_nonnull (T* p)
913{
914 gcc_assert (p);
915 return p;
916}
917
918// Returns true iff T is non-null and represents constraint info.
919inline tree_constraint_info *
920check_constraint_info (tree t)
921{
922 if (t && TREE_CODE (t) == CONSTRAINT_INFO)
923 return (tree_constraint_info *)t;
924 return NULL;
925}
926
927// Access the expression describing the template constraints. This may be
928// null if no constraints were introduced in the template parameter list,
929// a requirements clause after the template parameter list, or constraints
930// through a constrained-type-specifier.
931#define CI_TEMPLATE_REQS(NODE) \
932 check_constraint_info (check_nonnull(NODE))->template_reqs
933
934// Access the expression describing the trailing constraints. This is non-null
935// for any implicit instantiation of a constrained declaration. For a
936// templated declaration it is non-null only when a trailing requires-clause
937// was specified.
938#define CI_DECLARATOR_REQS(NODE) \
939 check_constraint_info (check_nonnull(NODE))->declarator_reqs
940
941// The computed associated constraint expression for a declaration.
942#define CI_ASSOCIATED_CONSTRAINTS(NODE) \
943 check_constraint_info (check_nonnull(NODE))->associated_constr
944
945// Access the logical constraints on the template parameters introduced
946// at a given template parameter list level indicated by NODE.
947#define TEMPLATE_PARMS_CONSTRAINTS(NODE) \
948 TREE_TYPE (TREE_LIST_CHECK (NODE))
949
950// Access the logical constraints on the template parameter declaration
951// indicated by NODE.
952#define TEMPLATE_PARM_CONSTRAINTS(NODE) \
953 TREE_TYPE (TREE_LIST_CHECK (NODE))
954
955/* Non-zero if the noexcept is present in a compound requirement. */
956#define COMPOUND_REQ_NOEXCEPT_P(NODE) \
957 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (TREE_CHECK (NODE, COMPOUND_REQ))
958
959/* The constraints on an 'auto' placeholder type, used in an argument deduction
960 constraint. */
961#define PLACEHOLDER_TYPE_CONSTRAINTS(NODE) \
962 DECL_SIZE_UNIT (TYPE_NAME (NODE))
963
964/* The expression evaluated by the predicate constraint. */
965#define PRED_CONSTR_EXPR(NODE) \
966 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, PRED_CONSTR), 0)
967
968/* The concept of a concept check. */
969#define CHECK_CONSTR_CONCEPT(NODE) \
970 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, CHECK_CONSTR), 0)
971
972/* The template arguments of a concept check. */
973#define CHECK_CONSTR_ARGS(NODE) \
974 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, CHECK_CONSTR), 1)
975
976/* The expression validated by the predicate constraint. */
977#define EXPR_CONSTR_EXPR(NODE) \
978 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, EXPR_CONSTR), 0)
979
980/* The type validated by the predicate constraint. */
981#define TYPE_CONSTR_TYPE(NODE) \
982 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, TYPE_CONSTR), 0)
983
984/* In an implicit conversion constraint, the source expression. */
985#define ICONV_CONSTR_EXPR(NODE) \
986 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, ICONV_CONSTR), 0)
987
988/* In an implicit conversion constraint, the target type. */
989#define ICONV_CONSTR_TYPE(NODE) \
990 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, ICONV_CONSTR), 1)
991
992/* In an argument deduction constraint, the source expression. */
993#define DEDUCT_CONSTR_EXPR(NODE) \
994 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, DEDUCT_CONSTR), 0)
995
996/* In an argument deduction constraint, the target type pattern. */
997#define DEDUCT_CONSTR_PATTERN(NODE) \
998 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, DEDUCT_CONSTR), 1)
999
1000/* In an argument deduction constraint, the list of placeholder nodes. */
1001#define DEDUCT_CONSTR_PLACEHOLDER(NODE) \
1002 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, DEDUCT_CONSTR), 2)
1003
1004/* The expression of an exception constraint. */
1005#define EXCEPT_CONSTR_EXPR(NODE) \
1006 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, EXCEPT_CONSTR), 0)
1007
1008/* In a parameterized constraint, the local parameters. */
1009#define PARM_CONSTR_PARMS(NODE) \
1010 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, PARM_CONSTR), 0)
1011
1012/* In a parameterized constraint, the operand. */
1013#define PARM_CONSTR_OPERAND(NODE) \
1014 TREE_OPERAND (TREE_CHECK (NODE, PARM_CONSTR), 1)
1015
1016/* Whether a PARM_DECL represents a local parameter in a
1017 requires-expression. */
1018#define CONSTRAINT_VAR_P(NODE) \
1019 DECL_LANG_FLAG_2 (TREE_CHECK (NODE, PARM_DECL))
1020
1021/* The concept constraining this constrained template-parameter. */
1022#define CONSTRAINED_PARM_CONCEPT(NODE) \
1023 DECL_SIZE_UNIT (TYPE_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
1024/* Any extra template arguments specified for a constrained
1025 template-parameter. */
1026#define CONSTRAINED_PARM_EXTRA_ARGS(NODE) \
1027 DECL_SIZE (TYPE_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
1028/* The first template parameter of CONSTRAINED_PARM_CONCEPT to be used as a
1029 prototype for the constrained parameter in finish_shorthand_constraint,
1030 attached for convenience. */
1031#define CONSTRAINED_PARM_PROTOTYPE(NODE) \
1032 DECL_INITIAL (TYPE_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
1033
1034enum cp_tree_node_structure_enum {
1035 TS_CP_GENERIC,
1036 TS_CP_IDENTIFIER,
1037 TS_CP_TPI,
1038 TS_CP_PTRMEM,
1039 TS_CP_BINDING,
1040 TS_CP_OVERLOAD,
1041 TS_CP_BASELINK,
1042 TS_CP_TEMPLATE_DECL,
1043 TS_CP_WRAPPER,
1044 TS_CP_DEFAULT_ARG,
1045 TS_CP_DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT,
1046 TS_CP_STATIC_ASSERT,
1047 TS_CP_ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT,
1048 TS_CP_TRAIT_EXPR,
1049 TS_CP_LAMBDA_EXPR,
1050 TS_CP_TEMPLATE_INFO,
1051 TS_CP_CONSTRAINT_INFO,
1052 TS_CP_USERDEF_LITERAL,
1053 LAST_TS_CP_ENUM
1054};

1056/* The resulting tree type. */
1057union GTY((desc ("cp_tree_node_structure (&%h)"),
1058 chain_next ("(union lang_tree_node *) c_tree_chain_next (&%h.generic)"))) lang_tree_node {
1059 union tree_node GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_GENERIC"),
1060 desc ("tree_node_structure (&%h)"))) generic;
1061 struct template_parm_index GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_TPI"))) tpi;
1062 struct ptrmem_cst GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_PTRMEM"))) ptrmem;
1063 struct tree_overload GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_OVERLOAD"))) overload;
1064 struct tree_baselink GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_BASELINK"))) baselink;
1065 struct tree_template_decl GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_TEMPLATE_DECL"))) template_decl;
1066 struct tree_default_arg GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_DEFAULT_ARG"))) default_arg;
1067 struct tree_deferred_noexcept GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT"))) deferred_noexcept;
1068 struct lang_identifier GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_IDENTIFIER"))) identifier;
1069 struct tree_static_assert GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_STATIC_ASSERT")))
1070 static_assertion;
1071 struct tree_argument_pack_select GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT")))
1072 argument_pack_select;
1073 struct tree_trait_expr GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_TRAIT_EXPR")))
1074 trait_expression;
1075 struct tree_lambda_expr GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_LAMBDA_EXPR")))
1076 lambda_expression;
1077 struct tree_template_info GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_TEMPLATE_INFO")))
1078 template_info;
1079 struct tree_constraint_info GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_CONSTRAINT_INFO")))
1080 constraint_info;
1081 struct tree_userdef_literal GTY ((tag ("TS_CP_USERDEF_LITERAL")))
1082 userdef_literal;
1083};

1352/* RAII sentinel to handle clearing processing_template_decl and restoring

1359 : saved (processing_template_decl)
1360 {
1361 if (reset)
1362 processing_template_decl = 0;
1363 }
1364 ~processing_template_decl_sentinel()
1365 {
1366 processing_template_decl = saved;
1367 }

1453/* The current C++-specific per-function global variables. */
1454
1455#define cp_function_chain (cfun->language)
1456
1457/* In a constructor destructor, the point at which all derived class
1458 destroying/construction has been done. I.e., just before a
1459 constructor returns, or before any base class destroying will be done
1460 in a destructor. */
1461
1462#define cdtor_label cp_function_chain->x_cdtor_label
1463
1464/* When we're processing a member function, current_class_ptr is the
1465 PARM_DECL for the `this' pointer. The current_class_ref is an
1466 expression for `*this'. */
1467
1468#define current_class_ptr \
1469 (*(cfun && cp_function_chain \
1470 ? &cp_function_chain->x_current_class_ptr \
1471 : &scope_chain->x_current_class_ptr))
1472#define current_class_ref \
1473 (*(cfun && cp_function_chain \
1474 ? &cp_function_chain->x_current_class_ref \
1475 : &scope_chain->x_current_class_ref))
1476
1477/* The EH_SPEC_BLOCK for the exception-specifiers for the current
1478 function, if any. */
1479
1480#define current_eh_spec_block cp_function_chain->x_eh_spec_block
1481
1482/* The `__in_chrg' parameter for the current function. Only used for
1483 constructors and destructors. */
1484
1485#define current_in_charge_parm cp_function_chain->x_in_charge_parm
1486
1487/* The `__vtt_parm' parameter for the current function. Only used for
1488 constructors and destructors. */
1489
1490#define current_vtt_parm cp_function_chain->x_vtt_parm
1491
1492/* Set to 0 at beginning of a function definition, set to 1 if
1493 a return statement that specifies a return value is seen. */
1494
1495#define current_function_returns_value cp_function_chain->returns_value
1496
1497/* Set to 0 at beginning of a function definition, set to 1 if
1498 a return statement with no argument is seen. */
1499
1500#define current_function_returns_null cp_function_chain->returns_null
1501
1502/* Set to 0 at beginning of a function definition, set to 1 if
1503 a call to a noreturn function is seen. */
1504
1505#define current_function_returns_abnormally \
1506 cp_function_chain->returns_abnormally
1507
1508/* Set to 0 at beginning of a function definition, set to 1 if we see an
1509 obvious infinite loop. This can have false positives and false
1510 negatives, so it should only be used as a heuristic. */
1511
1512#define current_function_infinite_loop cp_function_chain->infinite_loop
1513
1514/* Nonzero if we are processing a base initializer. Zero elsewhere. */
1515#define in_base_initializer cp_function_chain->x_in_base_initializer
1516
1517#define in_function_try_handler cp_function_chain->x_in_function_try_handler
1518
1519/* Expression always returned from function, or error_mark_node
1520 otherwise, for use by the automatic named return value optimization. */
1521
1522#define current_function_return_value \
1523 (cp_function_chain->x_return_value)
1524
1525/* A type involving 'auto' to be used for return type deduction. */
1526
1527#define current_function_auto_return_pattern \
1528 (cp_function_chain->x_auto_return_pattern)
1529
1530/* True if NAME is the IDENTIFIER_NODE for an overloaded "operator
1531 new" or "operator delete". */
1532#define NEW_DELETE_OPNAME_P(NAME) \
1533 ((NAME) == cp_operator_id (NEW_EXPR) \
1534 || (NAME) == cp_operator_id (VEC_NEW_EXPR) \
1535 || (NAME) == cp_operator_id (DELETE_EXPR) \
1536 || (NAME) == cp_operator_id (VEC_DELETE_EXPR))
1537
1538#define cp_operator_id(CODE) \
1539 (operator_name_info[(int) (CODE)].identifier)
1540#define cp_assignment_operator_id(CODE) \
1541 (assignment_operator_name_info[(int) (CODE)].identifier)
1542/* In parser.c. */
1543extern tree cp_literal_operator_id (const char *);
1544
1545/* TRUE if a tree code represents a statement. */
1546extern bool statement_code_p[MAX_TREE_CODES];
1547
1548#define STATEMENT_CODE_P(CODE) statement_code_p[(int) (CODE)]
1549
1550enum languages { lang_c, lang_cplusplus };
1551
1552/* Macros to make error reporting functions' lives easier. */
1553#define TYPE_LINKAGE_IDENTIFIER(NODE) \
1554 (TYPE_IDENTIFIER (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (NODE)))
1555#define TYPE_NAME_STRING(NODE) (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (TYPE_IDENTIFIER (NODE)))
1556#define TYPE_NAME_LENGTH(NODE) (IDENTIFIER_LENGTH (TYPE_IDENTIFIER (NODE)))
1557
1558/* Nonzero if NODE has no name for linkage purposes. */
1559#define TYPE_UNNAMED_P(NODE) \
1560 (OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (NODE) && anon_aggrname_p (TYPE_LINKAGE_IDENTIFIER (NODE)))
1561
1562/* The _DECL for this _TYPE. */
1563#define TYPE_MAIN_DECL(NODE) (TYPE_STUB_DECL (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (NODE)))
1564
1565/* Nonzero if T is a type that could resolve to any kind of concrete type
1566 at instantiation time. */
1567#define WILDCARD_TYPE_P(T) \
1568 (TREE_CODE (T) == TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM \
1569 || TREE_CODE (T) == TYPENAME_TYPE \
1570 || TREE_CODE (T) == TYPEOF_TYPE \
1571 || TREE_CODE (T) == BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM \
1572 || TREE_CODE (T) == DECLTYPE_TYPE)
1573
1574/* Nonzero if T is a class (or struct or union) type. Also nonzero
1575 for template type parameters, typename types, and instantiated
1576 template template parameters. Keep these checks in ascending code
1577 order. */
1578#define MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P(T) (WILDCARD_TYPE_P (T) || CLASS_TYPE_P (T))
1579
1580/* Set CLASS_TYPE_P for T to VAL. T must be a class, struct, or
1581 union type. */
1582#define SET_CLASS_TYPE_P(T, VAL) \
1583 (TYPE_LANG_FLAG_5 (T) = (VAL))
1584
1585/* Nonzero if T is a class type. Zero for template type parameters,
1586 typename types, and so forth. */
1587#define CLASS_TYPE_P(T) \
1588 (RECORD_OR_UNION_CODE_P (TREE_CODE (T)) && TYPE_LANG_FLAG_5 (T))
1589
1590/* Nonzero if T is a class type but not an union. */
1591#define NON_UNION_CLASS_TYPE_P(T) \
1592 (CLASS_TYPE_P (T) && TREE_CODE (T) != UNION_TYPE)
1593
1594/* Keep these checks in ascending code order. */
1595#define RECORD_OR_UNION_CODE_P(T) \
1596 ((T) == RECORD_TYPE || (T) == UNION_TYPE)
1597#define OVERLOAD_TYPE_P(T) \
1598 (CLASS_TYPE_P (T) || TREE_CODE (T) == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
1599
1600/* True if this type is dependent. This predicate is only valid if
1601 TYPE_DEPENDENT_P_VALID is true. */
1602#define TYPE_DEPENDENT_P(NODE) TYPE_LANG_FLAG_0 (NODE)
1603
1604/* True if dependent_type_p has been called for this type, with the
1605 result that TYPE_DEPENDENT_P is valid. */
1606#define TYPE_DEPENDENT_P_VALID(NODE) TYPE_LANG_FLAG_6(NODE)
1607
1608/* Nonzero if this type is const-qualified. */
1609#define CP_TYPE_CONST_P(NODE) \
1610 ((cp_type_quals (NODE) & TYPE_QUAL_CONST) != 0)
1611
1612/* Nonzero if this type is volatile-qualified. */
1613#define CP_TYPE_VOLATILE_P(NODE) \
1614 ((cp_type_quals (NODE) & TYPE_QUAL_VOLATILE) != 0)
1615
1616/* Nonzero if this type is restrict-qualified. */
1617#define CP_TYPE_RESTRICT_P(NODE) \
1618 ((cp_type_quals (NODE) & TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT) != 0)
1619
1620/* Nonzero if this type is const-qualified, but not
1621 volatile-qualified. Other qualifiers are ignored. This macro is
1622 used to test whether or not it is OK to bind an rvalue to a
1623 reference. */
1624#define CP_TYPE_CONST_NON_VOLATILE_P(NODE) \
1625 ((cp_type_quals (NODE) & (TYPE_QUAL_CONST | TYPE_QUAL_VOLATILE)) \
1626 == TYPE_QUAL_CONST)
1627
1628#define FUNCTION_ARG_CHAIN(NODE) \
1629 TREE_CHAIN (TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (NODE)))
1630
1631/* Given a FUNCTION_DECL, returns the first TREE_LIST out of TYPE_ARG_TYPES
1632 which refers to a user-written parameter. */
1633#define FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARMTYPE(NODE) \
1634 skip_artificial_parms_for ((NODE), TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (NODE)))
1635
1636/* Similarly, but for DECL_ARGUMENTS. */
1637#define FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARM(NODE) \
1638 skip_artificial_parms_for ((NODE), DECL_ARGUMENTS (NODE))
1639
1640/* Nonzero iff TYPE is derived from PARENT. Ignores accessibility and
1641 ambiguity issues. */
1642#define DERIVED_FROM_P(PARENT, TYPE) \
1643 (lookup_base ((TYPE), (PARENT), ba_any, NULL, tf_none) != NULL_TREE)
1644
1645/* Gives the visibility specification for a class type. */
1646#define CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY(TYPE) \
1647 DECL_VISIBILITY (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (TYPE))
1648#define CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED(TYPE) \
1649 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (TYPE))
1650
1651struct GTY (()) tree_pair_s {
1652 tree purpose;
1653 tree value;
1654};
1655typedef tree_pair_s *tree_pair_p;

1657/* This is a few header flags for 'struct lang_type'. Actually,
1658 all but the first are used only for lang_type_class; they
1659 are put in this structure to save space. */
1660struct GTY(()) lang_type_header {
1661 BOOL_BITFIELD is_lang_type_class : 1;
1662
1663 BOOL_BITFIELD has_type_conversion : 1;
1664 BOOL_BITFIELD has_copy_ctor : 1;
1665 BOOL_BITFIELD has_default_ctor : 1;
1666 BOOL_BITFIELD const_needs_init : 1;
1667 BOOL_BITFIELD ref_needs_init : 1;
1668 BOOL_BITFIELD has_const_copy_assign : 1;
1669
1670 BOOL_BITFIELD spare : 1;
1671};
1672
1673/* This structure provides additional information above and beyond
1674 what is provide in the ordinary tree_type. In the past, we used it
1675 for the types of class types, template parameters types, typename
1676 types, and so forth. However, there can be many (tens to hundreds
1677 of thousands) of template parameter types in a compilation, and
1678 there's no need for this additional information in that case.
1679 Therefore, we now use this data structure only for class types.
1680
1681 In the past, it was thought that there would be relatively few
1682 class types. However, in the presence of heavy use of templates,
1683 many (i.e., thousands) of classes can easily be generated.
1684 Therefore, we should endeavor to keep the size of this structure to
1685 a minimum. */
1686struct GTY(()) lang_type_class {
1687 struct lang_type_header h;
1688
1689 unsigned char align;
1690
1691 unsigned has_mutable : 1;
1692 unsigned com_interface : 1;
1693 unsigned non_pod_class : 1;
1694 unsigned nearly_empty_p : 1;
1695 unsigned user_align : 1;
1696 unsigned has_copy_assign : 1;
1697 unsigned has_new : 1;
1698 unsigned has_array_new : 1;
1699
1700 unsigned gets_delete : 2;
1701 unsigned interface_only : 1;
1702 unsigned interface_unknown : 1;
1703 unsigned contains_empty_class_p : 1;
1704 unsigned anon_aggr : 1;
1705 unsigned non_zero_init : 1;
1706 unsigned empty_p : 1;
1707
1708 unsigned vec_new_uses_cookie : 1;
1709 unsigned declared_class : 1;
1710 unsigned diamond_shaped : 1;
1711 unsigned repeated_base : 1;
1712 unsigned being_defined : 1;
1713 unsigned debug_requested : 1;
1714 unsigned fields_readonly : 1;
1715 unsigned ptrmemfunc_flag : 1;
1716
1717 unsigned use_template : 2;
1718 unsigned was_anonymous : 1;
1719 unsigned lazy_default_ctor : 1;
1720 unsigned lazy_copy_ctor : 1;
1721 unsigned lazy_copy_assign : 1;
1722 unsigned lazy_destructor : 1;
1723 unsigned has_const_copy_ctor : 1;
1724
1725 unsigned has_complex_copy_ctor : 1;
1726 unsigned has_complex_copy_assign : 1;
1727 unsigned non_aggregate : 1;
1728 unsigned has_complex_dflt : 1;
1729 unsigned has_list_ctor : 1;
1730 unsigned non_std_layout : 1;
1731 unsigned is_literal : 1;
1732 unsigned lazy_move_ctor : 1;
1733
1734 unsigned lazy_move_assign : 1;
1735 unsigned has_complex_move_ctor : 1;
1736 unsigned has_complex_move_assign : 1;
1737 unsigned has_constexpr_ctor : 1;
1738 unsigned unique_obj_representations : 1;
1739 unsigned unique_obj_representations_set : 1;
1740
1741 /* When adding a flag here, consider whether or not it ought to
1742 apply to a template instance if it applies to the template. If
1743 so, make sure to copy it in instantiate_class_template! */
1744
1745 /* There are some bits left to fill out a 32-bit word. Keep track
1746 of this by updating the size of this bitfield whenever you add or
1747 remove a flag. */
1748 unsigned dummy : 2;
1749
1750 tree primary_base;
1751 vec<tree_pair_s, va_gc> *vcall_indices;
1752 tree vtables;
1753 tree typeinfo_var;
1754 vec<tree, va_gc> *vbases;
1755 binding_table nested_udts;
1756 tree as_base;
1757 vec<tree, va_gc> *pure_virtuals;
1758 tree friend_classes;
1759 vec<tree, va_gc> * GTY((reorder ("resort_type_method_vec"))) methods;
1760 tree key_method;
1761 tree decl_list;
1762 tree template_info;
1763 tree befriending_classes;
1764 /* In a RECORD_TYPE, information specific to Objective-C++, such
1765 as a list of adopted protocols or a pointer to a corresponding
1766 @interface. See objc/objc-act.h for details. */
1767 tree objc_info;
1768 /* sorted_fields is sorted based on a pointer, so we need to be able
1769 to resort it if pointers get rearranged. */
1770 struct sorted_fields_type * GTY ((reorder ("resort_sorted_fields")))
1771 sorted_fields;
1772 /* FIXME reuse another field? */
1773 tree lambda_expr;
1774};
1775
1776struct GTY(()) lang_type_ptrmem {
1777 struct lang_type_header h;
1778 tree record;
1779};
1780
1781struct GTY(()) lang_type {
1782 union lang_type_u
1783 {
1784 struct lang_type_header GTY((skip (""))) h;
1785 struct lang_type_class GTY((tag ("1"))) c;
1786 struct lang_type_ptrmem GTY((tag ("0"))) ptrmem;
1787 } GTY((desc ("%h.h.is_lang_type_class"))) u;
1788};
1789
1790#if defined ENABLE_TREE_CHECKING && (GCC_VERSION >= 2007)
1791
1792#define LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK(NODE) __extension__ \
1793({ struct lang_type *lt = TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE); \
1794 if (! lt->u.h.is_lang_type_class) \
1795 lang_check_failed (__FILE__, __LINE__, __FUNCTION__); \
1796 &lt->u.c; })
1797
1798#define LANG_TYPE_PTRMEM_CHECK(NODE) __extension__ \
1799({ struct lang_type *lt = TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE); \
1800 if (lt->u.h.is_lang_type_class) \
1801 lang_check_failed (__FILE__, __LINE__, __FUNCTION__); \
1802 &lt->u.ptrmem; })
1803
1804#else
1805
1806#define LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK(NODE) (&TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.c)
1807#define LANG_TYPE_PTRMEM_CHECK(NODE) (&TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.ptrmem)
1808
1809#endif /* ENABLE_TREE_CHECKING */

1811/* Nonzero for _CLASSTYPE means that operator delete is defined. */
1812#define TYPE_GETS_DELETE(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->gets_delete)
1813#define TYPE_GETS_REG_DELETE(NODE) (TYPE_GETS_DELETE (NODE) & 1)

1815/* Nonzero if `new NODE[x]' should cause the allocation of extra
1816 storage to indicate how many array elements are in use. */
1817#define TYPE_VEC_NEW_USES_COOKIE(NODE) \
1818 (CLASS_TYPE_P (NODE) \
1819 && LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->vec_new_uses_cookie)

1821/* Nonzero means that this _CLASSTYPE node defines ways of converting
1822 itself to other types. */
1823#define TYPE_HAS_CONVERSION(NODE) \
1824 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->h.has_type_conversion)

1826/* Nonzero means that NODE (a class type) has a default constructor --
1827 but that it has not yet been declared. */
1828#define CLASSTYPE_LAZY_DEFAULT_CTOR(NODE) \
1829 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->lazy_default_ctor)
1830
1831/* Nonzero means that NODE (a class type) has a copy constructor --
1832 but that it has not yet been declared. */
1833#define CLASSTYPE_LAZY_COPY_CTOR(NODE) \
1834 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->lazy_copy_ctor)
1835
1836/* Nonzero means that NODE (a class type) has a move constructor --
1837 but that it has not yet been declared. */
1838#define CLASSTYPE_LAZY_MOVE_CTOR(NODE) \
1839 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->lazy_move_ctor)
1840
1841/* Nonzero means that NODE (a class type) has an assignment operator
1842 -- but that it has not yet been declared. */
1843#define CLASSTYPE_LAZY_COPY_ASSIGN(NODE) \
1844 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->lazy_copy_assign)
1845
1846/* Nonzero means that NODE (a class type) has an assignment operator
1847 -- but that it has not yet been declared. */
1848#define CLASSTYPE_LAZY_MOVE_ASSIGN(NODE) \
1849 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->lazy_move_assign)
1850
1851/* Nonzero means that NODE (a class type) has a destructor -- but that
1852 it has not yet been declared. */
1853#define CLASSTYPE_LAZY_DESTRUCTOR(NODE) \
1854 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->lazy_destructor)
1855
1856/* Nonzero means that NODE (a class type) is final */
1857#define CLASSTYPE_FINAL(NODE) \
1858 TYPE_FINAL_P (NODE)

1861/* Nonzero means that this _CLASSTYPE node overloads operator=(X&). */
1862#define TYPE_HAS_COPY_ASSIGN(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_copy_assign)
1863
1864/* True iff the class type NODE has an "operator =" whose parameter
1865 has a parameter of type "const X&". */
1866#define TYPE_HAS_CONST_COPY_ASSIGN(NODE) \

1868
1869/* Nonzero means that this _CLASSTYPE node has an X(X&) constructor. */
1870#define TYPE_HAS_COPY_CTOR(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->h.has_copy_ctor)
1871#define TYPE_HAS_CONST_COPY_CTOR(NODE) \
1872 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_const_copy_ctor)
1873
1874/* Nonzero if this class has an X(initializer_list<T>) constructor. */
1875#define TYPE_HAS_LIST_CTOR(NODE) \
1876 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_list_ctor)
1877
1878/* Nonzero if this class has a constexpr constructor other than a copy/move
1879 constructor. Note that a class can have constexpr constructors for
1880 static initialization even if it isn't a literal class. */
1881#define TYPE_HAS_CONSTEXPR_CTOR(NODE) \
1882 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_constexpr_ctor)
1883
1884/* Nonzero if this class defines an overloaded operator new. (An
1885 operator new [] doesn't count.) */
1886#define TYPE_HAS_NEW_OPERATOR(NODE) \
1887 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_new)
1888
1889/* Nonzero if this class defines an overloaded operator new[]. */
1890#define TYPE_HAS_ARRAY_NEW_OPERATOR(NODE) \
1891 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_array_new)
1892
1893/* Nonzero means that this type is being defined. I.e., the left brace
1894 starting the definition of this type has been seen. */
1895#define TYPE_BEING_DEFINED(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->being_defined)
1896
1897/* Nonzero means that this type is either complete or being defined, so we
1898 can do lookup in it. */
1899#define COMPLETE_OR_OPEN_TYPE_P(NODE) \
1900 (COMPLETE_TYPE_P (NODE) || (CLASS_TYPE_P (NODE) && TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (NODE)))

1902/* Mark bits for repeated base checks. */
1903#define TYPE_MARKED_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_6 (TYPE_CHECK (NODE))

1905/* Nonzero if the class NODE has multiple paths to the same (virtual)
1906 base object. */
1907#define CLASSTYPE_DIAMOND_SHAPED_P(NODE) \
1908 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK(NODE)->diamond_shaped)

1910/* Nonzero if the class NODE has multiple instances of the same base
1911 type. */

1915/* The member function with which the vtable will be emitted:
1916 the first noninline non-pure-virtual member function. NULL_TREE
1917 if there is no key function or if this is a class template */
1918#define CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->key_method)
1919
1920/* Vector member functions defined in this class. Each element is
1921 either a FUNCTION_DECL, a TEMPLATE_DECL, or an OVERLOAD. All
1922 functions with the same name end up in the same slot. The first
1923 two elements are for constructors, and destructors, respectively.
1924 All template conversion operators to innermost template dependent
1925 types are overloaded on the next slot, if they exist. Note, the
1926 names for these functions will not all be the same. The
1927 non-template conversion operators & templated conversions to
1928 non-innermost template types are next, followed by ordinary member
1929 functions. There may be empty entries at the end of the vector.
1930 The conversion operators are unsorted. The ordinary member
1931 functions are sorted, once the class is complete. */
1932#define CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->methods)
1933
1934/* For class templates, this is a TREE_LIST of all member data,
1935 functions, types, and friends in the order of declaration.
1936 The TREE_PURPOSE of each TREE_LIST is NULL_TREE for a friend,
1937 and the RECORD_TYPE for the class template otherwise. */
1938#define CLASSTYPE_DECL_LIST(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->decl_list)
1939
1940/* The slot in the CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC where constructors go. */
1941#define CLASSTYPE_CONSTRUCTOR_SLOT 0
1942
1943/* The slot in the CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC where destructors go. */
1944#define CLASSTYPE_DESTRUCTOR_SLOT 1
1945
1946/* The first slot in the CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC where conversion
1947 operators can appear. */
1948#define CLASSTYPE_FIRST_CONVERSION_SLOT 2
1949
1950/* A FUNCTION_DECL or OVERLOAD for the constructors for NODE. These
1951 are the constructors that take an in-charge parameter. */
1952#define CLASSTYPE_CONSTRUCTORS(NODE) \
1953 ((*CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC (NODE))[CLASSTYPE_CONSTRUCTOR_SLOT])
1954
1955/* A FUNCTION_DECL for the destructor for NODE. These are the
1956 destructors that take an in-charge parameter. If
1957 CLASSTYPE_LAZY_DESTRUCTOR is true, then this entry will be NULL
1958 until the destructor is created with lazily_declare_fn. */
1959#define CLASSTYPE_DESTRUCTORS(NODE) \
1960 (CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC (NODE) \
1961 ? (*CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC (NODE))[CLASSTYPE_DESTRUCTOR_SLOT] \
1962 : NULL_TREE)
1963
1964/* A dictionary of the nested user-defined-types (class-types, or enums)
1965 found within this class. This table includes nested member class
1966 templates. */
1967#define CLASSTYPE_NESTED_UTDS(NODE) \
1968 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->nested_udts)
1969
1970/* Nonzero if NODE has a primary base class, i.e., a base class with
1971 which it shares the virtual function table pointer. */
1972#define CLASSTYPE_HAS_PRIMARY_BASE_P(NODE) \
1973 (CLASSTYPE_PRIMARY_BINFO (NODE) != NULL_TREE)
1974
1975/* If non-NULL, this is the binfo for the primary base class, i.e.,
1976 the base class which contains the virtual function table pointer
1977 for this class. */
1978#define CLASSTYPE_PRIMARY_BINFO(NODE) \
1979 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->primary_base)

1981/* A vector of BINFOs for the direct and indirect virtual base classes
1982 that this type uses in a post-order depth-first left-to-right
1983 order. (In other words, these bases appear in the order that they
1984 should be initialized.) */
1985#define CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->vbases)
1986
1987/* The type corresponding to NODE when NODE is used as a base class,
1988 i.e., NODE without virtual base classes or tail padding. */
1989
1990#define CLASSTYPE_AS_BASE(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->as_base)

1992/* True iff NODE is the CLASSTYPE_AS_BASE version of some type. */

1996 && TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE) && CLASS_TYPE_P (TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE)) \
1997 && CLASSTYPE_AS_BASE (TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE)) == (NODE))

1999/* These are the size and alignment of the type without its virtual

2004#define CLASSTYPE_USER_ALIGN(NODE) TYPE_USER_ALIGN (CLASSTYPE_AS_BASE (NODE))

2103/* Nonzero if this class is included from a header file which employs

2108/* True if we have already determined whether or not vtables, VTTs,

2111 these items should be emitted; it only indicates that we know one
2112 way or the other. */
2113#define CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN(NODE) \
2114 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->interface_unknown == 0)

2121#define SET_CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_UNKNOWN(NODE) \

2123#define SET_CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN(NODE) \
2124 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->interface_unknown = 0)
