2132/* Nonzero means that this class is on a path leading to a new vtable. */
2133#define BINFO_VTABLE_PATH_MARKED(NODE) BINFO_FLAG_1 (NODE)
2134
2135/* Nonzero means B (a BINFO) has its own vtable. Any copies will not
2136 have this flag set. */
2137#define BINFO_NEW_VTABLE_MARKED(B) (BINFO_FLAG_2 (B))
2138
2139/* Compare a BINFO_TYPE with another type for equality. For a binfo,
2140 this is functionally equivalent to using same_type_p, but
2141 measurably faster. At least one of the arguments must be a
2142 BINFO_TYPE. The other can be a BINFO_TYPE or a regular type. If
2143 BINFO_TYPE(T) ever stops being the main variant of the class the
2144 binfo is for, this macro must change. */
2145#define SAME_BINFO_TYPE_P(A, B) ((A) == (B))
2146
2147/* Any subobject that needs a new vtable must have a vptr and must not
2148 be a non-virtual primary base (since it would then use the vtable from a
2149 derived class and never become non-primary.) */
2150#define SET_BINFO_NEW_VTABLE_MARKED(B) \
2151 (BINFO_NEW_VTABLE_MARKED (B) = 1, \
2152 gcc_assert (!BINFO_PRIMARY_P (B) || BINFO_VIRTUAL_P (B)), \
2153 gcc_assert (TYPE_VFIELD (BINFO_TYPE (B))))
2154
2155/* Nonzero if this binfo is for a dependent base - one that should not
2156 be searched. */
2157#define BINFO_DEPENDENT_BASE_P(NODE) BINFO_FLAG_3 (NODE)
2158
2159/* Nonzero if this binfo has lost its primary base binfo (because that
2160 is a nearly-empty virtual base that has been taken by some other
2161 base in the complete hierarchy. */
2162#define BINFO_LOST_PRIMARY_P(NODE) BINFO_FLAG_4 (NODE)
2163
2164/* Nonzero if this BINFO is a primary base class. */
2165#define BINFO_PRIMARY_P(NODE) BINFO_FLAG_5(NODE)
2166
2167/* Used by various search routines. */
2168#define IDENTIFIER_MARKED(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (NODE)
2169
2170/* A vec<tree_pair_s> of the vcall indices associated with the class
2171 NODE. The PURPOSE of each element is a FUNCTION_DECL for a virtual
2172 function. The VALUE is the index into the virtual table where the
2173 vcall offset for that function is stored, when NODE is a virtual
2174 base. */
2175#define CLASSTYPE_VCALL_INDICES(NODE) \
2176 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->vcall_indices)
2177
2178/* The various vtables for the class NODE. The primary vtable will be
2179 first, followed by the construction vtables and VTT, if any. */
2180#define CLASSTYPE_VTABLES(NODE) \
2181 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->vtables)
2182
2183/* The std::type_info variable representing this class, or NULL if no
2184 such variable has been created. This field is only set for the
2185 TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT of the class. */
2186#define CLASSTYPE_TYPEINFO_VAR(NODE) \
2187 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->typeinfo_var)
2188
2189/* Accessor macros for the BINFO_VIRTUALS list. */
2190
2191/* The number of bytes by which to adjust the `this' pointer when
2192 calling this virtual function. Subtract this value from the this
2193 pointer. Always non-NULL, might be constant zero though. */
2194#define BV_DELTA(NODE) (TREE_PURPOSE (NODE))
2195
2196/* If non-NULL, the vtable index at which to find the vcall offset
2197 when calling this virtual function. Add the value at that vtable
2198 index to the this pointer. */
2199#define BV_VCALL_INDEX(NODE) (TREE_TYPE (NODE))
2200
2201/* The function to call. */
2202#define BV_FN(NODE) (TREE_VALUE (NODE))
2203
2204/* Whether or not this entry is for a lost primary virtual base. */
2205#define BV_LOST_PRIMARY(NODE) (TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (NODE))
2206
2207/* For FUNCTION_TYPE or METHOD_TYPE, a list of the exceptions that
2208 this type can raise. Each TREE_VALUE is a _TYPE. The TREE_VALUE
2209 will be NULL_TREE to indicate a throw specification of `()', or
2210 no exceptions allowed. For a noexcept specification, TREE_VALUE
2211 is NULL_TREE and TREE_PURPOSE is the constant-expression. For
2212 a deferred noexcept-specification, TREE_PURPOSE is a DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT
2213 (for templates) or an OVERLOAD list of functions (for implicitly
2214 declared functions). */
2215#define TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS(NODE) \
2216 TYPE_LANG_SLOT_1 (FUNC_OR_METHOD_CHECK (NODE))
2217
2218/* For FUNCTION_TYPE or METHOD_TYPE, return 1 iff it is declared `throw()'
2219 or noexcept(true). */
2220#define TYPE_NOTHROW_P(NODE) nothrow_spec_p (TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (NODE))
2221
2222/* For FUNCTION_TYPE or METHOD_TYPE, true if NODE is noexcept. This is the
2223 case for things declared noexcept(true) and, with -fnothrow-opt, for
2224 throw() functions. */
2225#define TYPE_NOEXCEPT_P(NODE) type_noexcept_p (NODE)
2226
2227/* The binding level associated with the namespace. */
2228#define NAMESPACE_LEVEL(NODE) \
2229 (LANG_DECL_NS_CHECK (NODE)->level)
2230
2231/* Flags shared by all forms of DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC.
2232
2233 Some of the flags live here only to make lang_decl_min/fn smaller. Do
2234 not make this struct larger than 32 bits; instead, make sel smaller. */
2235
2236struct GTY(()) lang_decl_base {
2237 unsigned selector : 16; /* Larger than necessary for faster access. */
2238 ENUM_BITFIELD(languages) language : 1;
2239 unsigned use_template : 2;
2240 unsigned not_really_extern : 1; /* var or fn */
2241 unsigned initialized_in_class : 1; /* var or fn */
2242 unsigned repo_available_p : 1; /* var or fn */
2243 unsigned threadprivate_or_deleted_p : 1; /* var or fn */
2244 unsigned anticipated_p : 1; /* fn, type or template */
2245 /* anticipated_p reused as DECL_OMP_PRIVATIZED_MEMBER in var */
2246 unsigned friend_or_tls : 1; /* var, fn, type or template */
2247 unsigned template_conv_p : 1; /* var or template */
2248 unsigned odr_used : 1; /* var or fn */
2249 unsigned u2sel : 1;
2250 unsigned concept_p : 1; /* applies to vars and functions */
2251 unsigned var_declared_inline_p : 1; /* var */
2252 unsigned decomposition_p : 1; /* var */
2253 /* 1 spare bit */
2254};
2255
2256/* True for DECL codes which have template info and access. */
2257#define LANG_DECL_HAS_MIN(NODE) \
2258 (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (NODE) \
2259 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == FIELD_DECL \
2260 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == CONST_DECL \
2261 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_DECL \
2262 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == TEMPLATE_DECL \
2263 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == USING_DECL)
2264
2265/* DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC for the above codes. */
2266
2267struct GTY(()) lang_decl_min {
2268 struct lang_decl_base base;
2269
2270 /* In a FUNCTION_DECL for which DECL_THUNK_P holds, this is
2271 THUNK_ALIAS.
2272 In a FUNCTION_DECL for which DECL_THUNK_P does not hold,
2273 VAR_DECL, TYPE_DECL, or TEMPLATE_DECL, this is
2274 DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO. */
2275 tree template_info;
2276
2277 union lang_decl_u2 {
2278 /* In a FUNCTION_DECL for which DECL_THUNK_P holds, this is
2279 THUNK_VIRTUAL_OFFSET.
2280 Otherwise this is DECL_ACCESS. */
2281 tree GTY ((tag ("0"))) access;
2282
2283 /* For VAR_DECL in function, this is DECL_DISCRIMINATOR. */
2284 int GTY ((tag ("1"))) discriminator;
2285 } GTY ((desc ("%0.u.base.u2sel"))) u2;
2286};
2287
2288/* Additional DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC information for functions. */
2289
2290struct GTY(()) lang_decl_fn {
2291 struct lang_decl_min min;
2292
2293 /* In an overloaded operator, this is the value of
2294 DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P. */
2295 ENUM_BITFIELD (tree_code) operator_code : 16;
2296
2297 unsigned global_ctor_p : 1;
2298 unsigned global_dtor_p : 1;
2299 unsigned assignment_operator_p : 1;
2300 unsigned static_function : 1;
2301 unsigned pure_virtual : 1;
2302 unsigned defaulted_p : 1;
2303
2304 unsigned has_in_charge_parm_p : 1;
2305 unsigned has_vtt_parm_p : 1;
2306 unsigned pending_inline_p : 1;
2307 unsigned nonconverting : 1;
2308 unsigned thunk_p : 1;
2309 unsigned this_thunk_p : 1;
2310 unsigned hidden_friend_p : 1;
2311 unsigned omp_declare_reduction_p : 1;
2312 /* 2 spare bits on 32-bit hosts, 34 on 64-bit hosts. */
2313
2314 /* For a non-thunk function decl, this is a tree list of
2315 friendly classes. For a thunk function decl, it is the
2316 thunked to function decl. */
2317 tree befriending_classes;
2318
2319 /* For a non-virtual FUNCTION_DECL, this is
2320 DECL_FRIEND_CONTEXT. For a virtual FUNCTION_DECL for which
2321 DECL_THIS_THUNK_P does not hold, this is DECL_THUNKS. Both
2322 this pointer and result pointer adjusting thunks are
2323 chained here. This pointer thunks to return pointer thunks
2324 will be chained on the return pointer thunk. */
2325 tree context;
2326
2327 union lang_decl_u5
2328 {
2329 /* In a non-thunk FUNCTION_DECL or TEMPLATE_DECL, this is
2330 DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION. */
2331 tree GTY ((tag ("0"))) cloned_function;
2332
2333 /* In a FUNCTION_DECL for which THUNK_P holds this is the
2334 THUNK_FIXED_OFFSET. */
2335 HOST_WIDE_INT GTY ((tag ("1"))) fixed_offset;
2336 } GTY ((desc ("%1.thunk_p"))) u5;
2337
2338 union lang_decl_u3
2339 {
2340 struct cp_token_cache * GTY ((tag ("1"))) pending_inline_info;
2341 struct language_function * GTY ((tag ("0")))
2342 saved_language_function;
2343 } GTY ((desc ("%1.pending_inline_p"))) u;
2344
2345};
2346
2347/* DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC for namespaces. */
2348
2349struct GTY(()) lang_decl_ns {
2350 struct lang_decl_base base;
2351 cp_binding_level *level;
2352 tree ns_using;
2353 tree ns_users;
2354};
2355
2356/* DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC for parameters. */
2357
2358struct GTY(()) lang_decl_parm {
2359 struct lang_decl_base base;
2360 int level;
2361 int index;
2362};
2363
2364/* DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC for all types. It would be nice to just make this a
2365 union rather than a struct containing a union as its only field, but
2366 tree.h declares it as a struct. */
2367
2368struct GTY(()) lang_decl {
2369 union GTY((desc ("%h.base.selector"))) lang_decl_u {
2370 struct lang_decl_base GTY ((default)) base;
2371 struct lang_decl_min GTY((tag ("0"))) min;
2372 struct lang_decl_fn GTY ((tag ("1"))) fn;
2373 struct lang_decl_ns GTY((tag ("2"))) ns;
2374 struct lang_decl_parm GTY((tag ("3"))) parm;
2375 } u;
2376};
2377
2378/* Looks through a template (if present) to find what it declares. */
2379#define STRIP_TEMPLATE(NODE) \
2380 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == TEMPLATE_DECL ? DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (NODE) : NODE)
2381
2382#if defined ENABLE_TREE_CHECKING && (GCC_VERSION >= 2007)
2383
2384#define LANG_DECL_MIN_CHECK(NODE) __extension__ \
2385({ struct lang_decl *lt = DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE); \
2386 if (!LANG_DECL_HAS_MIN (NODE)) \
2387 lang_check_failed (__FILE__, __LINE__, __FUNCTION__); \
2388 &lt->u.min; })
2389
2390/* We want to be able to check DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P and such on a function
2391 template, not just on a FUNCTION_DECL. So when looking for things in
2392 lang_decl_fn, look down through a TEMPLATE_DECL into its result. */
2393#define LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK(NODE) __extension__ \
2394({ struct lang_decl *lt = DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (STRIP_TEMPLATE (NODE)); \
2395 if (!DECL_DECLARES_FUNCTION_P (NODE) || lt->u.base.selector != 1) \
2396 lang_check_failed (__FILE__, __LINE__, __FUNCTION__); \
2397 &lt->u.fn; })
2398
2399#define LANG_DECL_NS_CHECK(NODE) __extension__ \
2400({ struct lang_decl *lt = DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE); \
2401 if (TREE_CODE (NODE) != NAMESPACE_DECL || lt->u.base.selector != 2) \
2402 lang_check_failed (__FILE__, __LINE__, __FUNCTION__); \
2403 &lt->u.ns; })
2404
2405#define LANG_DECL_PARM_CHECK(NODE) __extension__ \
2406({ struct lang_decl *lt = DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE); \
2407 if (TREE_CODE (NODE) != PARM_DECL) \
2408 lang_check_failed (__FILE__, __LINE__, __FUNCTION__); \
2409 &lt->u.parm; })
2410
2411#define LANG_DECL_U2_CHECK(NODE, TF) __extension__ \
2412({ struct lang_decl *lt = DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE); \
2413 if (!LANG_DECL_HAS_MIN (NODE) || lt->u.base.u2sel != TF) \
2414 lang_check_failed (__FILE__, __LINE__, __FUNCTION__); \
2415 &lt->u.min.u2; })
2416
2417#else
2418
2419#define LANG_DECL_MIN_CHECK(NODE) \
2420 (&DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.min)
2421
2422#define LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK(NODE) \
2423 (&DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (STRIP_TEMPLATE (NODE))->u.fn)
2424
2425#define LANG_DECL_NS_CHECK(NODE) \
2426 (&DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.ns)
2427
2428#define LANG_DECL_PARM_CHECK(NODE) \
2429 (&DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.parm)
2430
2431#define LANG_DECL_U2_CHECK(NODE, TF) \
2432 (&DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.min.u2)
2433
2434#endif /* ENABLE_TREE_CHECKING */
2435
2436/* For a FUNCTION_DECL or a VAR_DECL, the language linkage for the
2437 declaration. Some entities (like a member function in a local
2438 class, or a local variable) do not have linkage at all, and this
2439 macro should not be used in those cases.
2440
2441 Implementation note: A FUNCTION_DECL without DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC was
2442 created by language-independent code, and has C linkage. Most
2443 VAR_DECLs have C++ linkage, and do not have DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC, but
2444 we do create DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC for variables with non-C++ linkage. */
2445#define DECL_LANGUAGE(NODE) \
2446 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE) \
2447 ? DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.base.language \
2448 : (TREE_CODE (NODE) == FUNCTION_DECL \
2449 ? lang_c : lang_cplusplus))
2450
2451/* Set the language linkage for NODE to LANGUAGE. */
2452#define SET_DECL_LANGUAGE(NODE, LANGUAGE) \
2453 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.base.language = (LANGUAGE))
2454
2455/* For FUNCTION_DECLs and TEMPLATE_DECLs: nonzero means that this function
2456 is a constructor. */
2457#define DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2458 DECL_CXX_CONSTRUCTOR_P (STRIP_TEMPLATE (NODE))
2459
2460/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a constructor for a complete
2461 object. */
2462#define DECL_COMPLETE_CONSTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2463 (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2464 && DECL_NAME (NODE) == complete_ctor_identifier)
2465
2466/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a constructor for a base
2467 object. */
2468#define DECL_BASE_CONSTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2469 (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2470 && DECL_NAME (NODE) == base_ctor_identifier)
2471
2472/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a constructor, but not either the
2473 specialized in-charge constructor or the specialized not-in-charge
2474 constructor. */
2475#define DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_CONSTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2476 (DECL_DECLARES_FUNCTION_P (NODE) && DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2477 && !DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (NODE))
2478
2479/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a copy constructor. */
2480#define DECL_COPY_CONSTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2481 (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (NODE) && copy_fn_p (NODE) > 0)
2482
2483/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a move constructor. */
2484#define DECL_MOVE_CONSTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2485 (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (NODE) && move_fn_p (NODE))
2486
2487/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL or TEMPLATE_DECL)
2488 is a destructor. */
2489#define DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2490 DECL_CXX_DESTRUCTOR_P (STRIP_TEMPLATE (NODE))
2491
2492/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a destructor, but not the
2493 specialized in-charge constructor, in-charge deleting constructor,
2494 or the base destructor. */
2495#define DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_DESTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2496 (DECL_DECLARES_FUNCTION_P (NODE) && DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2497 && !DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (NODE))
2498
2499/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a destructor for a complete
2500 object. */
2501#define DECL_COMPLETE_DESTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2502 (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2503 && DECL_NAME (NODE) == complete_dtor_identifier)
2504
2505/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a destructor for a base
2506 object. */
2507#define DECL_BASE_DESTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2508 (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2509 && DECL_NAME (NODE) == base_dtor_identifier)
2510
2511/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a destructor for a complete
2512 object that deletes the object after it has been destroyed. */
2513#define DECL_DELETING_DESTRUCTOR_P(NODE) \
2514 (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2515 && DECL_NAME (NODE) == deleting_dtor_identifier)
2516
2517/* Nonzero if NODE (a FUNCTION_DECL) is a cloned constructor or
2518 destructor. */
2519#define DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P(NODE) (!!decl_cloned_function_p (NODE, true))
2520
2521/* If DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P holds, this is the function that was
2522 cloned. */
2523#define DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION(NODE) (*decl_cloned_function_p (NODE, false))
2524
2525/* Perform an action for each clone of FN, if FN is a function with
2526 clones. This macro should be used like:
2527
2528 FOR_EACH_CLONE (clone, fn)
2529 { ... }
2530
2531 */
2532#define FOR_EACH_CLONE(CLONE, FN) \
2533 if (!(TREE_CODE (FN) == FUNCTION_DECL \
2534 && (DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (FN) \
2535 || DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_DESTRUCTOR_P (FN))))\
2536 ; \
2537 else \
2538 for (CLONE = DECL_CHAIN (FN); \
2539 CLONE && DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (CLONE); \
2540 CLONE = DECL_CHAIN (CLONE))
2541
2542/* Nonzero if NODE has DECL_DISCRIMINATOR and not DECL_ACCESS. */
2543#define DECL_DISCRIMINATOR_P(NODE) \
2544 (VAR_P (NODE) && DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (NODE))
2545
2546/* Discriminator for name mangling. */
2547#define DECL_DISCRIMINATOR(NODE) (LANG_DECL_U2_CHECK (NODE, 1)->discriminator)
2548
2549/* True iff DECL_DISCRIMINATOR is set for a DECL_DISCRIMINATOR_P decl. */
2550#define DECL_DISCRIMINATOR_SET_P(NODE) \
2551 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE) && DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.base.u2sel == 1)
2552
2553/* The index of a user-declared parameter in its function, starting at 1.
2554 All artificial parameters will have index 0. */
2555#define DECL_PARM_INDEX(NODE) \
2556 (LANG_DECL_PARM_CHECK (NODE)->index)
2557
2558/* The level of a user-declared parameter in its function, starting at 1.
2559 A parameter of the function will have level 1; a parameter of the first
2560 nested function declarator (i.e. t in void f (void (*p)(T t))) will have
2561 level 2. */
2562#define DECL_PARM_LEVEL(NODE) \
2563 (LANG_DECL_PARM_CHECK (NODE)->level)
2564
2565/* Nonzero if the VTT parm has been added to NODE. */
2566#define DECL_HAS_VTT_PARM_P(NODE) \
2567 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->has_vtt_parm_p)
2568
2569/* Nonzero if NODE is a FUNCTION_DECL for which a VTT parameter is
2570 required. */
2571#define DECL_NEEDS_VTT_PARM_P(NODE) \
2572 (CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (DECL_CONTEXT (NODE)) \
2573 && (DECL_BASE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2574 || DECL_BASE_DESTRUCTOR_P (NODE)))
2575
2576/* Nonzero if NODE is a user-defined conversion operator. */
2577#define DECL_CONV_FN_P(NODE) \
2578 (DECL_NAME (NODE) && IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P (DECL_NAME (NODE)))
2579
2580/* If FN is a conversion operator, the type to which it converts.
2581 Otherwise, NULL_TREE. */
2582#define DECL_CONV_FN_TYPE(FN) \
2583 (DECL_CONV_FN_P (FN) ? TREE_TYPE (DECL_NAME (FN)) : NULL_TREE)
2584
2585/* Nonzero if NODE, which is a TEMPLATE_DECL, is a template
2586 conversion operator to a type dependent on the innermost template
2587 args. */
2588#define DECL_TEMPLATE_CONV_FN_P(NODE) \
2589 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (TEMPLATE_DECL_CHECK (NODE))->u.base.template_conv_p)
2590
2591/* Nonzero if NODE, a static data member, was declared in its class as an
2592 array of unknown bound. */
2593#define VAR_HAD_UNKNOWN_BOUND(NODE) \
2594 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE)) \
2595 ? DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.base.template_conv_p \
2596 : false)
2597#define SET_VAR_HAD_UNKNOWN_BOUND(NODE) \
2598 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE))->u.base.template_conv_p = true)
2599
2600/* Set the overloaded operator code for NODE to CODE. */
2601#define SET_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_CODE(NODE, CODE) \
2602 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->operator_code = (CODE))
2603
2604/* If NODE is an overloaded operator, then this returns the TREE_CODE
2605 associated with the overloaded operator.
2606 DECL_ASSIGNMENT_OPERATOR_P must also be checked to determine
2607 whether or not NODE is an assignment operator. If NODE is not an
2608 overloaded operator, ERROR_MARK is returned. Since the numerical
2609 value of ERROR_MARK is zero, this macro can be used as a predicate
2610 to test whether or not NODE is an overloaded operator. */
2611#define DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P(NODE) \
2612 (IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (DECL_NAME (NODE)) \
2613 ? LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->operator_code : ERROR_MARK)
2614
2615/* Nonzero if NODE is an assignment operator (including += and such). */
2616#define DECL_ASSIGNMENT_OPERATOR_P(NODE) \
2617 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->assignment_operator_p)
2618
2619/* For FUNCTION_DECLs: nonzero means that this function is a
2620 constructor or a destructor with an extra in-charge parameter to
2621 control whether or not virtual bases are constructed. */
2622#define DECL_HAS_IN_CHARGE_PARM_P(NODE) \
2623 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->has_in_charge_parm_p)
2624
2625/* Nonzero if DECL is a declaration of __builtin_constant_p. */
2626#define DECL_IS_BUILTIN_CONSTANT_P(NODE) \
2627 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == FUNCTION_DECL \
2628 && DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (NODE) == BUILT_IN_NORMAL \
2629 && DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (NODE) == BUILT_IN_CONSTANT_P)
2630
2631/* Nonzero for _DECL means that this decl appears in (or will appear
2632 in) as a member in a RECORD_TYPE or UNION_TYPE node. It is also for
2633 detecting circularity in case members are multiply defined. In the
2634 case of a VAR_DECL, it is also used to determine how program storage
2635 should be allocated. */
2636#define DECL_IN_AGGR_P(NODE) (DECL_LANG_FLAG_3 (NODE))
2637
2638/* Nonzero for a VAR_DECL means that the variable's initialization (if
2639 any) has been processed. (In general, DECL_INITIALIZED_P is
2640 !DECL_EXTERNAL, but static data members may be initialized even if
2641 not defined.) */
2642#define DECL_INITIALIZED_P(NODE) \
2643 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE)))
2644
2645/* Nonzero for a VAR_DECL iff an explicit initializer was provided
2646 or a non-trivial constructor is called. */
2647#define DECL_NONTRIVIALLY_INITIALIZED_P(NODE) \
2648 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_3 (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE)))
2649
2650/* Nonzero for a VAR_DECL that was initialized with a
2651 constant-expression. */
2652#define DECL_INITIALIZED_BY_CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_P(NODE) \
2653 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_2 (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE)))
2654
2655/* Nonzero if the DECL was initialized in the class definition itself,
2656 rather than outside the class. This is used for both static member
2657 VAR_DECLS, and FUNCTION_DECLS that are defined in the class. */
2658#define DECL_INITIALIZED_IN_CLASS_P(DECL) \
2659 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_CHECK (DECL)) \
2660 ->u.base.initialized_in_class)
2661
2662/* Nonzero if the DECL is used in the sense of 3.2 [basic.def.odr].
2663 Only available for decls with DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC. */
2664#define DECL_ODR_USED(DECL) \
2665 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_CHECK (DECL)) \
2666 ->u.base.odr_used)
2667
2668/* Nonzero for DECL means that this decl is just a friend declaration,
2669 and should not be added to the list of members for this class. */
2670#define DECL_FRIEND_P(NODE) \
2671 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (TYPE_FUNCTION_OR_TEMPLATE_DECL_CHECK (NODE)) \
2672 ->u.base.friend_or_tls)
2673
2674/* Nonzero if the thread-local variable was declared with __thread as
2675 opposed to thread_local. */
2676#define DECL_GNU_TLS_P(NODE) \
2677 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE)) \
2678 && DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.base.friend_or_tls)
2679#define SET_DECL_GNU_TLS_P(NODE) \
2680 (retrofit_lang_decl (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE)), \
2681 DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.base.friend_or_tls = true)
2682
2683/* A TREE_LIST of the types which have befriended this FUNCTION_DECL. */
2684#define DECL_BEFRIENDING_CLASSES(NODE) \
2685 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->befriending_classes)
2686
2687/* Nonzero for FUNCTION_DECL means that this decl is a static
2688 member function. */
2689#define DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P(NODE) \
2690 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->static_function)
2691
2692/* Nonzero for FUNCTION_DECL means that this decl is a non-static
2693 member function. */
2694#define DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P(NODE) \
2695 (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (NODE)) == METHOD_TYPE)
2696
2697/* Nonzero for FUNCTION_DECL means that this decl is a member function
2698 (static or non-static). */
2699#define DECL_FUNCTION_MEMBER_P(NODE) \
2700 (DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (NODE) || DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (NODE))
2701
2702/* Nonzero for FUNCTION_DECL means that this member function
2703 has `this' as const X *const. */
2704#define DECL_CONST_MEMFUNC_P(NODE) \
2705 (DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (NODE) \
2706 && CP_TYPE_CONST_P (TREE_TYPE (TREE_VALUE \
2707 (TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (NODE))))))
2708
2709/* Nonzero for FUNCTION_DECL means that this member function
2710 has `this' as volatile X *const. */
2711#define DECL_VOLATILE_MEMFUNC_P(NODE) \
2712 (DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (NODE) \
2713 && CP_TYPE_VOLATILE_P (TREE_TYPE (TREE_VALUE \
2714 (TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (NODE))))))
2715
2716/* Nonzero for a DECL means that this member is a non-static member. */
2717#define DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_P(NODE) \
2718 (DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (NODE) \
2719 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == FIELD_DECL)
2720
2721/* Nonzero for _DECL means that this member object type
2722 is mutable. */
2723#define DECL_MUTABLE_P(NODE) (DECL_LANG_FLAG_0 (NODE))
2724
2725/* Nonzero for _DECL means that this constructor or conversion function is
2726 non-converting. */
2727#define DECL_NONCONVERTING_P(NODE) \
2728 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->nonconverting)
2729
2730/* Nonzero for FUNCTION_DECL means that this member function is a pure
2731 virtual function. */
2732#define DECL_PURE_VIRTUAL_P(NODE) \
2733 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->pure_virtual)
2734
2735/* True (in a FUNCTION_DECL) if NODE is a virtual function that is an
2736 invalid overrider for a function from a base class. Once we have
2737 complained about an invalid overrider we avoid complaining about it
2738 again. */
2739#define DECL_INVALID_OVERRIDER_P(NODE) \
2740 (DECL_LANG_FLAG_4 (NODE))
2741
2742/* True (in a FUNCTION_DECL) if NODE is a function declared with
2743 an override virt-specifier */
2744#define DECL_OVERRIDE_P(NODE) (TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (NODE))
2745
2746/* The thunks associated with NODE, a FUNCTION_DECL. */
2747#define DECL_THUNKS(NODE) \
2748 (DECL_VIRTUAL_P (NODE) ? LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->context : NULL_TREE)
2749
2750/* Set DECL_THUNKS. */
2751#define SET_DECL_THUNKS(NODE,THUNKS) \
2752 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->context = (THUNKS))
2753
2754/* If NODE, a FUNCTION_DECL, is a C++11 inheriting constructor, then this
2755 is the constructor it inherits from. */
2756#define DECL_INHERITED_CTOR(NODE) \
2757 (DECL_DECLARES_FUNCTION_P (NODE) && DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (NODE) \
2758 ? LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->context : NULL_TREE)
2759
2760/* And this is the base that constructor comes from. */
2761#define DECL_INHERITED_CTOR_BASE(NODE) \
2762 (DECL_INHERITED_CTOR (NODE) \
2763 ? DECL_CONTEXT (flag_new_inheriting_ctors \
2764 ? strip_inheriting_ctors (NODE) \
2765 : DECL_INHERITED_CTOR (NODE)) \
2766 : NULL_TREE)
2767
2768/* Set the inherited base. */
2769#define SET_DECL_INHERITED_CTOR(NODE,INH) \
2770 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->context = (INH))
2771
2772/* Nonzero if NODE is a thunk, rather than an ordinary function. */
2773#define DECL_THUNK_P(NODE) \
2774 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == FUNCTION_DECL \
2775 && DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE) \
2776 && LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->thunk_p)
2777
2778/* Set DECL_THUNK_P for node. */
2779#define SET_DECL_THUNK_P(NODE, THIS_ADJUSTING) \
2780 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->thunk_p = 1, \
2781 LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->this_thunk_p = (THIS_ADJUSTING))
2782
2783/* Nonzero if NODE is a this pointer adjusting thunk. */
2784#define DECL_THIS_THUNK_P(NODE) \
2785 (DECL_THUNK_P (NODE) && LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->this_thunk_p)
2786
2787/* Nonzero if NODE is a result pointer adjusting thunk. */
2788#define DECL_RESULT_THUNK_P(NODE) \
2789 (DECL_THUNK_P (NODE) && !LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->this_thunk_p)
2790
2791/* Nonzero if NODE is a FUNCTION_DECL, but not a thunk. */
2792#define DECL_NON_THUNK_FUNCTION_P(NODE) \
2793 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == FUNCTION_DECL && !DECL_THUNK_P (NODE))
2794
2795/* Nonzero if NODE is `extern "C"'. */
2796#define DECL_EXTERN_C_P(NODE) \
2797 (DECL_LANGUAGE (NODE) == lang_c)
2798
2799/* Nonzero if NODE is an `extern "C"' function. */
2800#define DECL_EXTERN_C_FUNCTION_P(NODE) \
2801 (DECL_NON_THUNK_FUNCTION_P (NODE) && DECL_EXTERN_C_P (NODE))
2802
2803/* True iff DECL is an entity with vague linkage whose definition is
2804 available in this translation unit. */
2805#define DECL_REPO_AVAILABLE_P(NODE) \
2806 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.base.repo_available_p)
2807
2808/* True if DECL is declared 'constexpr'. */
2809#define DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P(DECL) \
2810 DECL_LANG_FLAG_8 (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_CHECK (STRIP_TEMPLATE (DECL)))
2811
2812// True if NODE was declared as 'concept'. The flag implies that the
2813// declaration is constexpr, that the declaration cannot be specialized or
2814// refined, and that the result type must be convertible to bool.
2815#define DECL_DECLARED_CONCEPT_P(NODE) \
2816 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.base.concept_p)
2817
2818/* Nonzero if this DECL is the __PRETTY_FUNCTION__ variable in a
2819 template function. */
2820#define DECL_PRETTY_FUNCTION_P(NODE) \
2821 (DECL_NAME (NODE) \
2822 && !strcmp (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_NAME (NODE)), "__PRETTY_FUNCTION__"))
2823
2824/* Nonzero if the variable was declared to be thread-local.
2825 We need a special C++ version of this test because the middle-end
2826 DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P uses the symtab, so we can't use it for
2827 templates. */
2828#define CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P(NODE) \
2829 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE)))
2830
2831/* The _TYPE context in which this _DECL appears. This field holds the
2832 class where a virtual function instance is actually defined. */
2833#define DECL_CLASS_CONTEXT(NODE) \
2834 (DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (NODE) ? DECL_CONTEXT (NODE) : NULL_TREE)
2835
2836/* For a non-member friend function, the class (if any) in which this
2837 friend was defined. For example, given:
2838
2839 struct S { friend void f (); };
2840
2841 the DECL_FRIEND_CONTEXT for `f' will be `S'. */
2842#define DECL_FRIEND_CONTEXT(NODE) \
2843 ((DECL_DECLARES_FUNCTION_P (NODE) \
2844 && DECL_FRIEND_P (NODE) && !DECL_FUNCTION_MEMBER_P (NODE)) \
2845 ? LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->context \
2846 : NULL_TREE)
2847
2848/* Set the DECL_FRIEND_CONTEXT for NODE to CONTEXT. */
2849#define SET_DECL_FRIEND_CONTEXT(NODE, CONTEXT) \
2850 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (NODE)->context = (CONTEXT))
2851
2852#define CP_DECL_CONTEXT(NODE) \
2853 (!DECL_FILE_SCOPE_P (NODE) ? DECL_CONTEXT (NODE) : global_namespace)
2854#define CP_TYPE_CONTEXT(NODE) \
2855 (!TYPE_FILE_SCOPE_P (NODE) ? TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE) : global_namespace)
2856#define FROB_CONTEXT(NODE) \
2857 ((NODE) == global_namespace ? DECL_CONTEXT (NODE) : (NODE))
2858
2859/* 1 iff NODE has namespace scope, including the global namespace. */
2860#define DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P(NODE) \
2861 (!DECL_TEMPLATE_PARM_P (NODE) \
2862 && TREE_CODE (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (NODE)) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
2863
2864#define TYPE_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P(NODE) \
2865 (TREE_CODE (CP_TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE)) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
2866
2867#define NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P(NODE) \
2868 ((DECL_P (NODE) && DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (NODE)) \
2869 || (TYPE_P (NODE) && TYPE_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (NODE)))
2870
2871/* 1 iff NODE is a class member. */
2872#define DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P(NODE) \
2873 (DECL_CONTEXT (NODE) && TYPE_P (DECL_CONTEXT (NODE)))
2874
2875#define TYPE_CLASS_SCOPE_P(NODE) \
2876 (TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE) && TYPE_P (TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE)))
2877
2878/* 1 iff NODE is function-local. */
2879#define DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P(NODE) \
2880 (DECL_CONTEXT (NODE) \
2881 && TREE_CODE (DECL_CONTEXT (NODE)) == FUNCTION_DECL)
2882
2883#define TYPE_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P(NODE) \
2884 (TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE) && TREE_CODE (TYPE_CONTEXT (NODE)) == FUNCTION_DECL)
2885
2886/* 1 iff VAR_DECL node NODE is a type-info decl. This flag is set for

2888#define DECL_TINFO_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_4 (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
2889
2890/* 1 iff VAR_DECL node NODE is virtual table or VTT. */
2891#define DECL_VTABLE_OR_VTT_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_5 (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
2892
2893/* 1 iff FUNCTION_TYPE or METHOD_TYPE has a ref-qualifier (either & or &&). */
2894#define FUNCTION_REF_QUALIFIED(NODE) \
2895 TREE_LANG_FLAG_4 (FUNC_OR_METHOD_CHECK (NODE))
2896
2897/* 1 iff FUNCTION_TYPE or METHOD_TYPE has &&-ref-qualifier. */
2898#define FUNCTION_RVALUE_QUALIFIED(NODE) \

2900
2901/* Returns 1 iff VAR_DECL is a construction virtual table.

2903 before using this macro. */
2904#define DECL_CONSTRUCTION_VTABLE_P(NODE) \
2905 TREE_LANG_FLAG_6 (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
2906
2907/* 1 iff NODE is function-local, but for types. */
2908#define LOCAL_CLASS_P(NODE) \

2911/* For a NAMESPACE_DECL: the list of using namespace directives

2940#define TREE_INDIRECT_USING(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (TREE_LIST_CHECK (NODE))
2941
2942/* In a TREE_LIST in an attribute list, indicates that the attribute
2943 must be applied at instantiation time. */
2944#define ATTR_IS_DEPENDENT(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (TREE_LIST_CHECK (NODE))
2945

2947 was inherited from a template parameter, not explicitly indicated. */
2948#define ABI_TAG_IMPLICIT(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (TREE_LIST_CHECK (NODE))

2950extern tree decl_shadowed_for_var_lookup (tree);

2978/* In a FUNCTION_DECL, this is nonzero if this function was defined in

2985 function. */

2989/* Nonzero for TYPE_DECL means that it was written 'using name = type'. */
2990#define TYPE_DECL_ALIAS_P(NODE) \
2991 DECL_LANG_FLAG_6 (TYPE_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
2992
2993/* Nonzero for TEMPLATE_DECL means that it is a 'complex' alias template. */
2994#define TEMPLATE_DECL_COMPLEX_ALIAS_P(NODE) \
2995 DECL_LANG_FLAG_2 (TEMPLATE_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
2996
2997/* Nonzero for a type which is an alias for another type; i.e, a type
2998 which declaration was written 'using name-of-type =
2999 another-type'. */
3000#define TYPE_ALIAS_P(NODE) \
3001 (TYPE_P (NODE) \
3002 && TYPE_NAME (NODE) \
3003 && TREE_CODE (TYPE_NAME (NODE)) == TYPE_DECL \
3004 && TYPE_DECL_ALIAS_P (TYPE_NAME (NODE)))
3005
3006/* For a class type: if this structure has many fields, we'll sort them
3007 and put them into a TREE_VEC. */
3008#define CLASSTYPE_SORTED_FIELDS(NODE) \
3009 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->sorted_fields)
3010
3011/* If non-NULL for a VAR_DECL, FUNCTION_DECL, TYPE_DECL or
3012 TEMPLATE_DECL, the entity is either a template specialization (if
3013 DECL_USE_TEMPLATE is nonzero) or the abstract instance of the
3014 template itself.
3015
3016 In either case, DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO is a TREE_LIST, whose
3017 TREE_PURPOSE is the TEMPLATE_DECL of which this entity is a
3018 specialization or abstract instance. The TREE_VALUE is the
3019 template arguments used to specialize the template.
3020
3021 Consider:
3022
3023 template <typename T> struct S { friend void f(T) {} };
3024
3025 In this case, S<int>::f is, from the point of view of the compiler,
3026 an instantiation of a template -- but, from the point of view of
3027 the language, each instantiation of S results in a wholly unrelated
3028 global function f. In this case, DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO for S<int>::f
3029 will be non-NULL, but DECL_USE_TEMPLATE will be zero. */
3030#define DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO(NODE) \
3031 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (VAR_TEMPL_TYPE_FIELD_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_CHECK (NODE)) \
3032 ->u.min.template_info)
3033
3034/* For a VAR_DECL, indicates that the variable is actually a
3035 non-static data member of anonymous union that has been promoted to
3036 variable status. */
3037#define DECL_ANON_UNION_VAR_P(NODE) \
3038 (DECL_LANG_FLAG_4 (VAR_DECL_CHECK (NODE)))
3039
3040/* Template information for a RECORD_TYPE or UNION_TYPE. */
3041#define CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO(NODE) \
3042 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (RECORD_OR_UNION_CHECK (NODE))->template_info)
3043
3044/* Template information for an ENUMERAL_TYPE. Although an enumeration may
3045 not be a primary template, it may be declared within the scope of a
3046 primary template and the enumeration constants may depend on
3047 non-type template parameters. */
3048#define ENUM_TEMPLATE_INFO(NODE) \
3049 (TYPE_LANG_SLOT_1 (ENUMERAL_TYPE_CHECK (NODE)))
3050
3051/* Template information for a template template parameter. */
3052#define TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM_TEMPLATE_INFO(NODE) \
3053 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM_TYPE_CHECK (NODE)) \
3054 ->template_info)
3055
3056/* Template information for an ENUMERAL_, RECORD_, UNION_TYPE, or
3057 BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM type. This ignores any alias
3058 templateness of NODE. */
3059#define TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO(NODE) \
3060 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == ENUMERAL_TYPE \
3061 ? ENUM_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE) \
3062 : (TREE_CODE (NODE) == BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM \
3063 ? TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE) \
3064 : (CLASS_TYPE_P (NODE) \
3065 ? CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE) \
3066 : NULL_TREE)))
3067
3068/* Template information (if any) for an alias type. */
3069#define TYPE_ALIAS_TEMPLATE_INFO(NODE) \
3070 (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (TYPE_NAME (NODE)) \
3071 ? DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (TYPE_NAME (NODE)) \
3072 : NULL_TREE)
3073
3074/* If NODE is a type alias, this accessor returns the template info
3075 for the alias template (if any). Otherwise behave as
3076 TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO. */
3077#define TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO_MAYBE_ALIAS(NODE) \
3078 (TYPE_ALIAS_P (NODE) \
3079 ? TYPE_ALIAS_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE) \
3080 : TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE))
3081
3082/* Set the template information for an ENUMERAL_, RECORD_, or
3083 UNION_TYPE to VAL. */
3084#define SET_TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO(NODE, VAL) \
3085 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == ENUMERAL_TYPE \
3086 ? (ENUM_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE) = (VAL)) \
3087 : ((CLASS_TYPE_P (NODE) && !TYPE_ALIAS_P (NODE)) \
3088 ? (CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE) = (VAL)) \
3089 : (DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (TYPE_NAME (NODE)) = (VAL))))
3090
3091#define TI_TEMPLATE(NODE) TREE_TYPE (TEMPLATE_INFO_CHECK (NODE))
3092#define TI_ARGS(NODE) TREE_CHAIN (TEMPLATE_INFO_CHECK (NODE))
3093#define TI_PENDING_TEMPLATE_FLAG(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (NODE)
3094/* For a given TREE_VEC containing a template argument list,
3095 this property contains the number of arguments that are not
3096 defaulted. */
3097#define NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT(NODE) TREE_CHAIN (TREE_VEC_CHECK (NODE))
3098/* Below are the setter and getter of the NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT
3099 property. */
3100#define SET_NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT(NODE, INT_VALUE) \
3101 NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT(NODE) = build_int_cst (NULL_TREE, INT_VALUE)
3102#if CHECKING_P
3103#define GET_NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT(NODE) \
3104 int_cst_value (NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT (NODE))
3105#else
3106#define GET_NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT(NODE) \
3107 NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT (NODE) \
3108 ? int_cst_value (NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT (NODE)) \
3109 : TREE_VEC_LENGTH (INNERMOST_TEMPLATE_ARGS (NODE))
3110#endif
3111/* The list of typedefs - used in the template - that need
3112 access checking at template instantiation time.
3113
3114 FIXME this should be associated with the TEMPLATE_DECL, not the
3115 TEMPLATE_INFO. */
3116#define TI_TYPEDEFS_NEEDING_ACCESS_CHECKING(NODE) \
3117 ((struct tree_template_info*)TEMPLATE_INFO_CHECK \
3118 (NODE))->typedefs_needing_access_checking
3119
3120/* We use TREE_VECs to hold template arguments. If there is only one
3121 level of template arguments, then the TREE_VEC contains the
3122 arguments directly. If there is more than one level of template
3123 arguments, then each entry in the TREE_VEC is itself a TREE_VEC,
3124 containing the template arguments for a single level. The first
3125 entry in the outer TREE_VEC is the outermost level of template
3126 parameters; the last is the innermost.
3127
3128 It is incorrect to ever form a template argument vector containing
3129 only one level of arguments, but which is a TREE_VEC containing as
3130 its only entry the TREE_VEC for that level.
3131
3132 For each TREE_VEC containing the template arguments for a single
3133 level, it's possible to get or set the number of non defaulted
3134 template arguments by using the accessor macros
3135 GET_NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT or
3136 SET_NON_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE_ARGS_COUNT. */
3137
3138/* Nonzero if the template arguments is actually a vector of vectors,
3139 rather than just a vector. */
3140#define TMPL_ARGS_HAVE_MULTIPLE_LEVELS(NODE) \
3141 (NODE && TREE_VEC_LENGTH (NODE) && TREE_VEC_ELT (NODE, 0) \
3142 && TREE_CODE (TREE_VEC_ELT (NODE, 0)) == TREE_VEC)
3143
3144/* The depth of a template argument vector. When called directly by
3145 the parser, we use a TREE_LIST rather than a TREE_VEC to represent
3146 template arguments. In fact, we may even see NULL_TREE if there
3147 are no template arguments. In both of those cases, there is only
3148 one level of template arguments. */
3149#define TMPL_ARGS_DEPTH(NODE) \
3150 (TMPL_ARGS_HAVE_MULTIPLE_LEVELS (NODE) ? TREE_VEC_LENGTH (NODE) : 1)
3151
3152/* The LEVELth level of the template ARGS. The outermost level of
3153 args is level 1, not level 0. */
3154#define TMPL_ARGS_LEVEL(ARGS, LEVEL) \
3155 (TMPL_ARGS_HAVE_MULTIPLE_LEVELS (ARGS) \
3156 ? TREE_VEC_ELT (ARGS, (LEVEL) - 1) : (ARGS))
3157
3158/* Set the LEVELth level of the template ARGS to VAL. This macro does
3159 not work with single-level argument vectors. */
3160#define SET_TMPL_ARGS_LEVEL(ARGS, LEVEL, VAL) \
3161 (TREE_VEC_ELT (ARGS, (LEVEL) - 1) = (VAL))
3162
3163/* Accesses the IDXth parameter in the LEVELth level of the ARGS. */
3164#define TMPL_ARG(ARGS, LEVEL, IDX) \
3165 (TREE_VEC_ELT (TMPL_ARGS_LEVEL (ARGS, LEVEL), IDX))
3166
3167/* Given a single level of template arguments in NODE, return the
3168 number of arguments. */
3169#define NUM_TMPL_ARGS(NODE) \
3170 (TREE_VEC_LENGTH (NODE))
3171
3172/* Returns the innermost level of template arguments in ARGS. */
3173#define INNERMOST_TEMPLATE_ARGS(NODE) \
3174 (get_innermost_template_args ((NODE), 1))
3175
3176/* The number of levels of template parameters given by NODE. */
3177#define TMPL_PARMS_DEPTH(NODE) \
3178 ((HOST_WIDE_INT) TREE_INT_CST_LOW (TREE_PURPOSE (NODE)))
3179
3180/* The TEMPLATE_DECL instantiated or specialized by NODE. This
3181 TEMPLATE_DECL will be the immediate parent, not the most general
3182 template. For example, in:
3183
3184 template <class T> struct S { template <class U> void f(U); }
3185
3186 the FUNCTION_DECL for S<int>::f<double> will have, as its
3187 DECL_TI_TEMPLATE, `template <class U> S<int>::f<U>'.
3188
3189 As a special case, for a member friend template of a template
3190 class, this value will not be a TEMPLATE_DECL, but rather an
3191 IDENTIFIER_NODE or OVERLOAD indicating the name of the template and
3192 any explicit template arguments provided. For example, in:
3193
3194 template <class T> struct S { friend void f<int>(int, double); }
3195
3196 the DECL_TI_TEMPLATE will be an IDENTIFIER_NODE for `f' and the
3197 DECL_TI_ARGS will be {int}.
3198
3199 For a FIELD_DECL with a non-static data member initializer, this value
3200 is the FIELD_DECL it was instantiated from. */
3201#define DECL_TI_TEMPLATE(NODE) TI_TEMPLATE (DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE))
3202
3203/* The template arguments used to obtain this decl from the most
3204 general form of DECL_TI_TEMPLATE. For the example given for
3205 DECL_TI_TEMPLATE, the DECL_TI_ARGS will be {int, double}. These
3206 are always the full set of arguments required to instantiate this
3207 declaration from the most general template specialized here. */
3208#define DECL_TI_ARGS(NODE) TI_ARGS (DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE))
3209
3210/* The TEMPLATE_DECL associated with NODE, a class type. Even if NODE
3211 will be generated from a partial specialization, the TEMPLATE_DECL
3212 referred to here will be the original template. For example,
3213 given:
3214
3215 template <typename T> struct S {};
3216 template <typename T> struct S<T*> {};
3217
3218 the CLASSTPYE_TI_TEMPLATE for S<int*> will be S, not the S<T*>. */
3219#define CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE(NODE) TI_TEMPLATE (CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE))
3220#define CLASSTYPE_TI_ARGS(NODE) TI_ARGS (CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE))
3221
3222/* For a template instantiation TYPE, returns the TYPE corresponding
3223 to the primary template. Otherwise returns TYPE itself. */
3224#define CLASSTYPE_PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_TYPE(TYPE) \
3225 ((CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE ((TYPE)) \
3226 && !CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION ((TYPE))) \
3227 ? TREE_TYPE (DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (DECL_PRIMARY_TEMPLATE \
3228 (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE ((TYPE))))) \
3229 : (TYPE))
3230
3231/* Like CLASS_TI_TEMPLATE, but also works for ENUMERAL_TYPEs. */
3232#define TYPE_TI_TEMPLATE(NODE) \
3233 (TI_TEMPLATE (TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE)))
3234
3235/* Like DECL_TI_ARGS, but for an ENUMERAL_, RECORD_, or UNION_TYPE. */
3236#define TYPE_TI_ARGS(NODE) \
3237 (TI_ARGS (TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE)))
3238
3239#define INNERMOST_TEMPLATE_PARMS(NODE) TREE_VALUE (NODE)
3240
3241/* Nonzero if NODE (a TEMPLATE_DECL) is a member template, in the
3242 sense of [temp.mem]. */
3243#define DECL_MEMBER_TEMPLATE_P(NODE) \
3244 (DECL_LANG_FLAG_1 (TEMPLATE_DECL_CHECK (NODE)))
3245
3246/* Nonzero if the NODE corresponds to the template parameters for a
3247 member template, whose inline definition is being processed after
3248 the class definition is complete. */
3249#define TEMPLATE_PARMS_FOR_INLINE(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (NODE)
3250
3251/* Determine if a declaration (PARM_DECL or FIELD_DECL) is a pack. */
3252#define DECL_PACK_P(NODE) \
3253 (DECL_P (NODE) && PACK_EXPANSION_P (TREE_TYPE (NODE)))
3254
3255/* Determines if NODE is an expansion of one or more parameter packs,
3256 e.g., a TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION or EXPR_PACK_EXPANSION. */
3257#define PACK_EXPANSION_P(NODE) \
3258 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION \
3259 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == EXPR_PACK_EXPANSION)
3260
3261/* Extracts the type or expression pattern from a TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION or
3262 EXPR_PACK_EXPANSION. */
3263#define PACK_EXPANSION_PATTERN(NODE) \
3264 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION? TREE_TYPE (NODE) \
3265 : TREE_OPERAND (NODE, 0))
3266
3267/* Sets the type or expression pattern for a TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION or
3268 EXPR_PACK_EXPANSION. */
3269#define SET_PACK_EXPANSION_PATTERN(NODE,VALUE) \
3270 if (TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION) \
3271 TREE_TYPE (NODE) = VALUE; \
3272 else \
3273 TREE_OPERAND (NODE, 0) = VALUE
3274
3275/* The list of parameter packs used in the PACK_EXPANSION_* node. The
3276 TREE_VALUE of each TREE_LIST contains the parameter packs. */
3277#define PACK_EXPANSION_PARAMETER_PACKS(NODE) \
3278 *(TREE_CODE (NODE) == EXPR_PACK_EXPANSION \
3279 ? &TREE_OPERAND (NODE, 1) \
3280 : &TYPE_MINVAL (TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION_CHECK (NODE)))
3281
3282/* Any additional template args to be applied when substituting into
3283 the pattern, set by tsubst_pack_expansion for partial instantiations. */
3284#define PACK_EXPANSION_EXTRA_ARGS(NODE) \
3285 *(TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION \
3286 ? &TYPE_MAXVAL (NODE) \
3287 : &TREE_OPERAND ((NODE), 2))
3288
3289/* True iff this pack expansion is within a function context. */
3290#define PACK_EXPANSION_LOCAL_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (NODE)
3291
3292/* True iff this pack expansion is for sizeof.... */
3293#define PACK_EXPANSION_SIZEOF_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (NODE)
3294
3295/* True iff the wildcard can match a template parameter pack. */
3296#define WILDCARD_PACK_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (NODE)
3297
3298/* Determine if this is an argument pack. */
3299#define ARGUMENT_PACK_P(NODE) \
3300 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_ARGUMENT_PACK \
3301 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == NONTYPE_ARGUMENT_PACK)
3302
3303/* The arguments stored in an argument pack. Arguments are stored in a
3304 TREE_VEC, which may have length zero. */
3305#define ARGUMENT_PACK_ARGS(NODE) \
3306 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_ARGUMENT_PACK? TREE_TYPE (NODE) \
3307 : TREE_OPERAND (NODE, 0))
3308
3309/* Set the arguments stored in an argument pack. VALUE must be a
3310 TREE_VEC. */
3311#define SET_ARGUMENT_PACK_ARGS(NODE,VALUE) \
3312 if (TREE_CODE (NODE) == TYPE_ARGUMENT_PACK) \
3313 TREE_TYPE (NODE) = VALUE; \
3314 else \
3315 TREE_OPERAND (NODE, 0) = VALUE
3316
3317/* Whether the argument pack is "incomplete", meaning that more
3318 arguments can still be deduced. Incomplete argument packs are only
3319 used when the user has provided an explicit template argument list
3320 for a variadic function template. Some of the explicit template
3321 arguments will be placed into the beginning of the argument pack,
3322 but additional arguments might still be deduced. */
3323#define ARGUMENT_PACK_INCOMPLETE_P(NODE) \
3324 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (ARGUMENT_PACK_ARGS (NODE))
3325
3326/* When ARGUMENT_PACK_INCOMPLETE_P, stores the explicit template
3327 arguments used to fill this pack. */
3328#define ARGUMENT_PACK_EXPLICIT_ARGS(NODE) \
3329 TREE_TYPE (ARGUMENT_PACK_ARGS (NODE))
3330
3331/* In an ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT, the argument pack from which an
3332 argument will be selected. */
3333#define ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT_FROM_PACK(NODE) \
3334 (((struct tree_argument_pack_select *)ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT_CHECK (NODE))->argument_pack)
3335
3336/* In an ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT, the index of the argument we want to
3337 select. */
3338#define ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT_INDEX(NODE) \
3339 (((struct tree_argument_pack_select *)ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT_CHECK (NODE))->index)
3340
3341/* In an ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT, the actual underlying argument that the
3342 ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT represents. */
3343#define ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT_ARG(NODE) \
3344 TREE_VEC_ELT (ARGUMENT_PACK_ARGS (ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT_FROM_PACK (NODE)), \
3345 ARGUMENT_PACK_SELECT_INDEX (NODE))
3346
3347#define FOLD_EXPR_CHECK(NODE) \
3348 TREE_CHECK4 (NODE, UNARY_LEFT_FOLD_EXPR, UNARY_RIGHT_FOLD_EXPR, \
3349 BINARY_LEFT_FOLD_EXPR, BINARY_RIGHT_FOLD_EXPR)
3350
3351#define BINARY_FOLD_EXPR_CHECK(NODE) \
3352 TREE_CHECK2 (NODE, BINARY_LEFT_FOLD_EXPR, BINARY_RIGHT_FOLD_EXPR)
3353
3354/* True if NODE is UNARY_FOLD_EXPR or a BINARY_FOLD_EXPR */
3355#define FOLD_EXPR_P(NODE) \
3356 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == UNARY_LEFT_FOLD_EXPR \
3357 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == UNARY_RIGHT_FOLD_EXPR \
3358 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == BINARY_LEFT_FOLD_EXPR \
3359 || TREE_CODE (NODE) == BINARY_RIGHT_FOLD_EXPR)
3360
3361/* True when NODE is a fold over a compound assignment operator. */
3362#define FOLD_EXPR_MODIFY_P(NODE) \
3363 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (FOLD_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3364
3365/* An INTEGER_CST containing the tree code of the folded operator. */
3366#define FOLD_EXPR_OP(NODE) \
3367 TREE_OPERAND (FOLD_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 0)
3368
3369/* The expression containing an unexpanded parameter pack. */
3370#define FOLD_EXPR_PACK(NODE) \
3371 TREE_OPERAND (FOLD_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 1)
3372
3373/* In a binary fold expression, the argument with no unexpanded
3374 parameter packs. */
3375#define FOLD_EXPR_INIT(NODE) \
3376 TREE_OPERAND (BINARY_FOLD_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 2)
3377
3378/* In a FUNCTION_DECL, the saved language-specific per-function data. */
3379#define DECL_SAVED_FUNCTION_DATA(NODE) \
3380 (LANG_DECL_FN_CHECK (FUNCTION_DECL_CHECK (NODE)) \
3381 ->u.saved_language_function)
3382
3383/* True if NODE is an implicit INDIRECT_EXPR from convert_from_reference. */
3384#define REFERENCE_REF_P(NODE) \
3385 (INDIRECT_REF_P (NODE) \
3386 && TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (NODE, 0)) \
3387 && (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND ((NODE), 0))) \
3388 == REFERENCE_TYPE))
3389
3390/* True if NODE is a REFERENCE_TYPE which is OK to instantiate to be a
3391 reference to VLA type, because it's used for VLA capture. */
3392#define REFERENCE_VLA_OK(NODE) \
3393 (TYPE_LANG_FLAG_5 (REFERENCE_TYPE_CHECK (NODE)))
3394
3395#define NEW_EXPR_USE_GLOBAL(NODE) \
3396 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (NEW_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3397#define DELETE_EXPR_USE_GLOBAL(NODE) \
3398 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (DELETE_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3399#define DELETE_EXPR_USE_VEC(NODE) \
3400 TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (DELETE_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3401
3402#define CALL_OR_AGGR_INIT_CHECK(NODE) \
3403 TREE_CHECK2 ((NODE), CALL_EXPR, AGGR_INIT_EXPR)
3404
3405/* Indicates that this is a non-dependent COMPOUND_EXPR which will
3406 resolve to a function call. */
3407#define COMPOUND_EXPR_OVERLOADED(NODE) \
3408 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (COMPOUND_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3409
3410/* In a CALL_EXPR appearing in a template, true if Koenig lookup
3411 should be performed at instantiation time. */
3412#define KOENIG_LOOKUP_P(NODE) TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (CALL_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3413
3414/* True if the arguments to NODE should be evaluated in left-to-right
3415 order regardless of PUSH_ARGS_REVERSED. */
3416#define CALL_EXPR_ORDERED_ARGS(NODE) \
3417 TREE_LANG_FLAG_3 (CALL_OR_AGGR_INIT_CHECK (NODE))
3418
3419/* True if the arguments to NODE should be evaluated in right-to-left
3420 order regardless of PUSH_ARGS_REVERSED. */
3421#define CALL_EXPR_REVERSE_ARGS(NODE) \
3422 TREE_LANG_FLAG_5 (CALL_OR_AGGR_INIT_CHECK (NODE))
3423
3424/* True if CALL_EXPR was written as an operator expression, not a function
3425 call. */
3426#define CALL_EXPR_OPERATOR_SYNTAX(NODE) \
3427 TREE_LANG_FLAG_6 (CALL_OR_AGGR_INIT_CHECK (NODE))
3428
3429/* Indicates whether a string literal has been parenthesized. Such
3430 usages are disallowed in certain circumstances. */
3431
3432#define PAREN_STRING_LITERAL_P(NODE) \
3433 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (STRING_CST_CHECK (NODE))
3434
3435/* Indicates whether a COMPONENT_REF or a SCOPE_REF has been parenthesized, or
3436 an INDIRECT_REF comes from parenthesizing a _DECL. Currently only set some
3437 of the time in C++14 mode. */
3438
3439#define REF_PARENTHESIZED_P(NODE) \
3440 TREE_LANG_FLAG_2 (TREE_CHECK3 ((NODE), COMPONENT_REF, INDIRECT_REF, SCOPE_REF))
3441
3442/* Nonzero if this AGGR_INIT_EXPR provides for initialization via a
3443 constructor call, rather than an ordinary function call. */
3444#define AGGR_INIT_VIA_CTOR_P(NODE) \
3445 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (AGGR_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3446
3447/* Nonzero if expanding this AGGR_INIT_EXPR should first zero-initialize
3448 the object. */
3449#define AGGR_INIT_ZERO_FIRST(NODE) \
3450 TREE_LANG_FLAG_2 (AGGR_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3451
3452/* Nonzero means that the call is the jump from a thunk to the
3453 thunked-to function. */
3454#define AGGR_INIT_FROM_THUNK_P(NODE) \
3455 (AGGR_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE)->base.protected_flag)
3456
3457/* AGGR_INIT_EXPR accessors. These are equivalent to the CALL_EXPR
3458 accessors, except for AGGR_INIT_EXPR_SLOT (which takes the place of
3459 CALL_EXPR_STATIC_CHAIN). */
3460
3461#define AGGR_INIT_EXPR_FN(NODE) TREE_OPERAND (AGGR_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 1)
3462#define AGGR_INIT_EXPR_SLOT(NODE) \
3463 TREE_OPERAND (AGGR_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 2)
3464#define AGGR_INIT_EXPR_ARG(NODE, I) \
3465 TREE_OPERAND (AGGR_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), (I) + 3)
3466#define aggr_init_expr_nargs(NODE) (VL_EXP_OPERAND_LENGTH(NODE) - 3)
3467
3468/* AGGR_INIT_EXPR_ARGP returns a pointer to the argument vector for NODE.
3469 We can't use &AGGR_INIT_EXPR_ARG (NODE, 0) because that will complain if
3470 the argument count is zero when checking is enabled. Instead, do
3471 the pointer arithmetic to advance past the 3 fixed operands in a
3472 AGGR_INIT_EXPR. That produces a valid pointer to just past the end of
3473 the operand array, even if it's not valid to dereference it. */
3474#define AGGR_INIT_EXPR_ARGP(NODE) \
3475 (&(TREE_OPERAND (AGGR_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 0)) + 3)
3476
3477/* Abstract iterators for AGGR_INIT_EXPRs. */
3478
3479/* Structure containing iterator state. */
3480struct aggr_init_expr_arg_iterator {
3481 tree t; /* the aggr_init_expr */
3482 int n; /* argument count */
3483 int i; /* next argument index */
3484};
3485
3486/* Initialize the abstract argument list iterator object ITER with the
3487 arguments from AGGR_INIT_EXPR node EXP. */
3488inline void
3489init_aggr_init_expr_arg_iterator (tree exp,
3490 aggr_init_expr_arg_iterator *iter)
3491{
3492 iter->t = exp;
3493 iter->n = aggr_init_expr_nargs (exp);
3494 iter->i = 0;
3495}
3496
3497/* Return the next argument from abstract argument list iterator object ITER,
3498 and advance its state. Return NULL_TREE if there are no more arguments. */
3499inline tree
3500next_aggr_init_expr_arg (aggr_init_expr_arg_iterator *iter)
3501{
3502 tree result;
3503 if (iter->i >= iter->n)
3504 return NULL_TREE;
3505 result = AGGR_INIT_EXPR_ARG (iter->t, iter->i);
3506 iter->i++;
3507 return result;
3508}
3509
3510/* Initialize the abstract argument list iterator object ITER, then advance
3511 past and return the first argument. Useful in for expressions, e.g.
3512 for (arg = first_aggr_init_expr_arg (exp, &iter); arg;
3513 arg = next_aggr_init_expr_arg (&iter)) */
3514inline tree
3515first_aggr_init_expr_arg (tree exp, aggr_init_expr_arg_iterator *iter)
3516{
3517 init_aggr_init_expr_arg_iterator (exp, iter);
3518 return next_aggr_init_expr_arg (iter);
3519}
3520
3521/* Test whether there are more arguments in abstract argument list iterator
3522 ITER, without changing its state. */
3523inline bool
3524more_aggr_init_expr_args_p (const aggr_init_expr_arg_iterator *iter)
3525{
3526 return (iter->i < iter->n);
3527}
3528
3529/* Iterate through each argument ARG of AGGR_INIT_EXPR CALL, using variable
3530 ITER (of type aggr_init_expr_arg_iterator) to hold the iteration state. */
3531#define FOR_EACH_AGGR_INIT_EXPR_ARG(arg, iter, call) \
3532 for ((arg) = first_aggr_init_expr_arg ((call), &(iter)); (arg); \
3533 (arg) = next_aggr_init_expr_arg (&(iter)))
3534
3535/* VEC_INIT_EXPR accessors. */
3536#define VEC_INIT_EXPR_SLOT(NODE) TREE_OPERAND (VEC_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 0)
3537#define VEC_INIT_EXPR_INIT(NODE) TREE_OPERAND (VEC_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 1)
3538
3539/* Indicates that a VEC_INIT_EXPR is a potential constant expression.
3540 Only set when the current function is constexpr. */
3541#define VEC_INIT_EXPR_IS_CONSTEXPR(NODE) \
3542 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (VEC_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3543
3544/* Indicates that a VEC_INIT_EXPR is expressing value-initialization. */
3545#define VEC_INIT_EXPR_VALUE_INIT(NODE) \
3546 TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (VEC_INIT_EXPR_CHECK (NODE))
3547
3548/* The condition under which this MUST_NOT_THROW_EXPR actually blocks
3549 exceptions. NULL_TREE means 'true'. */
3550#define MUST_NOT_THROW_COND(NODE) \
3551 TREE_OPERAND (MUST_NOT_THROW_EXPR_CHECK (NODE), 1)
3552
3553/* The TYPE_MAIN_DECL for a class template type is a TYPE_DECL, not a
3554 TEMPLATE_DECL. This macro determines whether or not a given class
3555 type is really a template type, as opposed to an instantiation or
3556 specialization of one. */
3557#define CLASSTYPE_IS_TEMPLATE(NODE) \
3558 (CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE) \
3559 && !CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE (NODE) \
3560 && PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_P (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (NODE)))
3561
3562/* The name used by the user to name the typename type. Typically,

3565 TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR if we had something like `typename X::Y<T>'. */
3566#define TYPENAME_TYPE_FULLNAME(NODE) \
3567 (TYPE_VALUES_RAW (TYPENAME_TYPE_CHECK (NODE)))

3684/* Nonzero if DECL is explicitly defaulted in the class body. */
3685#define DECL_DEFAULTED_IN_CLASS_P(DECL) \

3687/* Nonzero if DECL was defaulted outside the class body. */
3688#define DECL_DEFAULTED_OUTSIDE_CLASS_P(DECL) \
3689 (DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (DECL) \
3690 && !(DECL_ARTIFICIAL (DECL) || DECL_INITIALIZED_IN_CLASS_P (DECL)))
3691
3692/* Record whether a typedef for type `int' was actually `signed int'. */
3693#define C_TYPEDEF_EXPLICITLY_SIGNED(EXP) DECL_LANG_FLAG_1 (EXP)
3694
3695/* Returns nonzero if DECL has external linkage, as specified by the
3696 language standard. (This predicate may hold even when the
3697 corresponding entity is not actually given external linkage in the
3698 object file; see decl_linkage for details.) */
3699#define DECL_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE_P(DECL) \
3700 (decl_linkage (DECL) == lk_external)
3701
3702/* Keep these codes in ascending code order. */
3703
3704#define INTEGRAL_CODE_P(CODE) \
3705 ((CODE) == ENUMERAL_TYPE \
3706 || (CODE) == BOOLEAN_TYPE \
3707 || (CODE) == INTEGER_TYPE)
3708
3709/* [basic.fundamental]
3710
3711 Types bool, char, wchar_t, and the signed and unsigned integer types
3712 are collectively called integral types.
3713
3714 Note that INTEGRAL_TYPE_P, as defined in tree.h, allows enumeration
3715 types as well, which is incorrect in C++. Keep these checks in
3716 ascending code order. */
3717#define CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P(TYPE) \
3718 (TREE_CODE (TYPE) == BOOLEAN_TYPE \
3719 || TREE_CODE (TYPE) == INTEGER_TYPE)
3720
3721/* Returns true if TYPE is an integral or enumeration name. Keep
3722 these checks in ascending code order. */
3723#define INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P(TYPE) \
3724 (TREE_CODE (TYPE) == ENUMERAL_TYPE || CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TYPE))
3725
3726/* Returns true if TYPE is an integral or unscoped enumeration type. */
3727#define INTEGRAL_OR_UNSCOPED_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P(TYPE) \
3728 (UNSCOPED_ENUM_P (TYPE) || CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TYPE))
3729
3730/* True if the class type TYPE is a literal type. */
3731#define CLASSTYPE_LITERAL_P(TYPE) \
3732 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (TYPE)->is_literal)
3733
3734/* [basic.fundamental]
3735
3736 Integral and floating types are collectively called arithmetic
3737 types.
3738
3739 As a GNU extension, we also accept complex types.
3740
3741 Keep these checks in ascending code order. */
3742#define ARITHMETIC_TYPE_P(TYPE) \
3743 (CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TYPE) \
3744 || TREE_CODE (TYPE) == REAL_TYPE \
3745 || TREE_CODE (TYPE) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
3746
3747/* True iff TYPE is cv decltype(nullptr). */
3748#define NULLPTR_TYPE_P(TYPE) (TREE_CODE (TYPE) == NULLPTR_TYPE)
3749
3750/* [basic.types]
3751
3752 Arithmetic types, enumeration types, pointer types,
3753 pointer-to-member types, and std::nullptr_t are collectively called
3754 scalar types.
3755
3756 Keep these checks in ascending code order. */
3757#define SCALAR_TYPE_P(TYPE) \
3758 (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (TYPE) \
3759 || TREE_CODE (TYPE) == ENUMERAL_TYPE \
3760 || ARITHMETIC_TYPE_P (TYPE) \
3761 || TYPE_PTR_P (TYPE) \
3762 || TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (TYPE) \
3763 || NULLPTR_TYPE_P (TYPE))
3764
3765/* Determines whether this type is a C++0x scoped enumeration
3766 type. Scoped enumerations types are introduced via "enum class" or
3767 "enum struct", e.g.,
3768
3769 enum class Color {
3770 Red, Green, Blue
3771 };
3772
3773 Scoped enumeration types are different from normal (unscoped)
3774 enumeration types in several ways:
3775
3776 - The enumerators of a scoped enumeration type are only available
3777 within the scope of the enumeration type and not in the
3778 enclosing scope. For example, the Red color can be referred to
3779 with "Color::Red" but not "Red".
3780
3781 - Scoped enumerators and enumerations do not implicitly convert
3782 to integers or 'bool'.
3783
3784 - The underlying type of the enum is well-defined. */
3785#define SCOPED_ENUM_P(TYPE) \
3786 (TREE_CODE (TYPE) == ENUMERAL_TYPE && ENUM_IS_SCOPED (TYPE))
3787
3788/* Determine whether this is an unscoped enumeration type. */
3789#define UNSCOPED_ENUM_P(TYPE) \
3790 (TREE_CODE (TYPE) == ENUMERAL_TYPE && !ENUM_IS_SCOPED (TYPE))
3791
3792/* Set the flag indicating whether an ENUMERAL_TYPE is a C++0x scoped
3793 enumeration type (1) or a normal (unscoped) enumeration type
3794 (0). */
3795#define SET_SCOPED_ENUM_P(TYPE, VAL) \
3796 (ENUM_IS_SCOPED (TYPE) = (VAL))
3797
3798#define SET_OPAQUE_ENUM_P(TYPE, VAL) \
3799 (ENUM_IS_OPAQUE (TYPE) = (VAL))
3800
3801#define OPAQUE_ENUM_P(TYPE) \
3802 (TREE_CODE (TYPE) == ENUMERAL_TYPE && ENUM_IS_OPAQUE (TYPE))
3803
3804/* Determines whether an ENUMERAL_TYPE has an explicit
3805 underlying type. */
3806#define ENUM_FIXED_UNDERLYING_TYPE_P(NODE) (TYPE_LANG_FLAG_5 (NODE))
3807
3808/* Returns the underlying type of the given enumeration type. The
3809 underlying type is determined in different ways, depending on the
3810 properties of the enum:
3811
3812 - In C++0x, the underlying type can be explicitly specified, e.g.,
3813
3814 enum E1 : char { ... } // underlying type is char
3815
3816 - In a C++0x scoped enumeration, the underlying type is int
3817 unless otherwises specified:
3818
3819 enum class E2 { ... } // underlying type is int
3820
3821 - Otherwise, the underlying type is determined based on the
3822 values of the enumerators. In this case, the
3823 ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE will not be set until after the definition
3824 of the enumeration is completed by finish_enum. */
3825#define ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE(TYPE) \
3826 TREE_TYPE (ENUMERAL_TYPE_CHECK (TYPE))
3827
3828/* [dcl.init.aggr]
3829
3830 An aggregate is an array or a class with no user-provided
3831 constructors, no brace-or-equal-initializers for non-static data
3832 members, no private or protected non-static data members, no
3833 base classes, and no virtual functions.
3834
3835 As an extension, we also treat vectors as aggregates. Keep these
3836 checks in ascending code order. */
3837#define CP_AGGREGATE_TYPE_P(TYPE) \
3838 (TREE_CODE (TYPE) == VECTOR_TYPE \
3839 ||TREE_CODE (TYPE) == ARRAY_TYPE \
3840 || (CLASS_TYPE_P (TYPE) && !CLASSTYPE_NON_AGGREGATE (TYPE)))
3841
3842/* Nonzero for a class type means that the class type has a
3843 user-declared constructor. */
3844#define TYPE_HAS_USER_CONSTRUCTOR(NODE) (TYPE_LANG_FLAG_1 (NODE))
3845
3846/* Nonzero means that the FUNCTION_TYPE or METHOD_TYPE has a
3847 late-specified return type. */
3848#define TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE(NODE) \
3849 (TYPE_LANG_FLAG_2 (FUNC_OR_METHOD_CHECK (NODE)))
3850
3851/* When appearing in an INDIRECT_REF, it means that the tree structure
3852 underneath is actually a call to a constructor. This is needed
3853 when the constructor must initialize local storage (which can
3854 be automatically destroyed), rather than allowing it to allocate
3855 space from the heap.
3856
3857 When appearing in a SAVE_EXPR, it means that underneath
3858 is a call to a constructor.
3859
3860 When appearing in a CONSTRUCTOR, the expression is a
3861 compound literal.
3862
3863 When appearing in a FIELD_DECL, it means that this field
3864 has been duly initialized in its constructor. */
3865#define TREE_HAS_CONSTRUCTOR(NODE) (TREE_LANG_FLAG_4 (NODE))
3866
3867/* True if NODE is a brace-enclosed initializer. */
3868#define BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P(NODE) \
3869 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == CONSTRUCTOR && TREE_TYPE (NODE) == init_list_type_node)
3870
3871/* True if NODE is a compound-literal, i.e., a brace-enclosed
3872 initializer cast to a particular type. */
3873#define COMPOUND_LITERAL_P(NODE) \
3874 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == CONSTRUCTOR && TREE_HAS_CONSTRUCTOR (NODE))
3875
3876#define EMPTY_CONSTRUCTOR_P(NODE) (TREE_CODE (NODE) == CONSTRUCTOR \
3877 && vec_safe_is_empty(CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS(NODE))\
3878 && !TREE_HAS_CONSTRUCTOR (NODE))
3879
3880/* True if NODE is a init-list used as a direct-initializer, i.e.
3881 B b{1,2}, not B b({1,2}) or B b = {1,2}. */
3882#define CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT(NODE) (TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (CONSTRUCTOR_CHECK (NODE)))
3883
3884/* True if an uninitialized element in NODE should not be treated as
3885 implicitly value-initialized. Only used in constexpr evaluation. */
3886#define CONSTRUCTOR_NO_IMPLICIT_ZERO(NODE) \
3887 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (CONSTRUCTOR_CHECK (NODE)))
3888
3889/* True if this CONSTRUCTOR should not be used as a variable initializer
3890 because it was loaded from a constexpr variable with mutable fields. */
3891#define CONSTRUCTOR_MUTABLE_POISON(NODE) \
3892 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_2 (CONSTRUCTOR_CHECK (NODE)))
3893
3894#define DIRECT_LIST_INIT_P(NODE) \
3895 (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (NODE) && CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (NODE))
3896
3897/* True if NODE represents a conversion for direct-initialization in a
3898 template. Set by perform_implicit_conversion_flags. */
3899#define IMPLICIT_CONV_EXPR_DIRECT_INIT(NODE) \
3900 (TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (IMPLICIT_CONV_EXPR_CHECK (NODE)))
3901
3902/* Nonzero means that an object of this type can not be initialized using
3903 an initializer list. */
3904#define CLASSTYPE_NON_AGGREGATE(NODE) \
3905 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->non_aggregate)
3906#define TYPE_NON_AGGREGATE_CLASS(NODE) \
3907 (CLASS_TYPE_P (NODE) && CLASSTYPE_NON_AGGREGATE (NODE))
3908
3909/* Nonzero if there is a non-trivial X::op=(cv X&) for this class. */
3910#define TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_COPY_ASSIGN(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_complex_copy_assign)
3911
3912/* Nonzero if there is a non-trivial X::X(cv X&) for this class. */
3913#define TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_COPY_CTOR(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_complex_copy_ctor)
3914
3915/* Nonzero if there is a non-trivial X::op=(X&&) for this class. */
3916#define TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_MOVE_ASSIGN(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_complex_move_assign)
3917
3918/* Nonzero if there is a non-trivial X::X(X&&) for this class. */
3919#define TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_MOVE_CTOR(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_complex_move_ctor)
3920
3921/* Nonzero if there is no trivial default constructor for this class. */
3922#define TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_DFLT(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->has_complex_dflt)
3923
3924/* Nonzero if TYPE has a trivial destructor. From [class.dtor]:
3925
3926 A destructor is trivial if it is an implicitly declared
3927 destructor and if:
3928
3929 - all of the direct base classes of its class have trivial
3930 destructors,
3931
3932 - for all of the non-static data members of its class that are
3933 of class type (or array thereof), each such class has a
3934 trivial destructor. */
3935#define TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR(NODE) \
3936 (!TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (NODE))
3937
3938/* Nonzero for _TYPE node means that this type does not have a trivial
3939 destructor. Therefore, destroying an object of this type will
3940 involve a call to a destructor. This can apply to objects of
3941 ARRAY_TYPE is the type of the elements needs a destructor. */
3942#define TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR(NODE) \
3943 (TYPE_LANG_FLAG_4 (NODE))
3944
3945/* Nonzero for class type means that the default constructor is trivial. */
3946#define TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DFLT(NODE) \
3947 (TYPE_HAS_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR (NODE) && ! TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_DFLT (NODE))
3948
3949/* Nonzero for class type means that copy initialization of this type can use
3950 a bitwise copy. */
3951#define TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_COPY_CTOR(NODE) \
3952 (TYPE_HAS_COPY_CTOR (NODE) && ! TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_COPY_CTOR (NODE))
3953
3954/* Nonzero for class type means that assignment of this type can use
3955 a bitwise copy. */
3956#define TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_COPY_ASSIGN(NODE) \
3957 (TYPE_HAS_COPY_ASSIGN (NODE) && ! TYPE_HAS_COMPLEX_COPY_ASSIGN (NODE))
3958
3959/* Returns true if NODE is a pointer-to-data-member. */
3960#define TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P(NODE) \
3961 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == OFFSET_TYPE)
3962/* Returns true if NODE is a pointer. */
3963#define TYPE_PTR_P(NODE) \
3964 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == POINTER_TYPE)
3965
3966/* Returns true if NODE is an object type:
3967
3968 [basic.types]
3969
3970 An object type is a (possibly cv-qualified) type that is not a
3971 function type, not a reference type, and not a void type.
3972
3973 Keep these checks in ascending order, for speed. */
3974#define TYPE_OBJ_P(NODE) \
3975 (TREE_CODE (NODE) != REFERENCE_TYPE \
3976 && !VOID_TYPE_P (NODE) \
3977 && TREE_CODE (NODE) != FUNCTION_TYPE \
3978 && TREE_CODE (NODE) != METHOD_TYPE)
3979
3980/* Returns true if NODE is a pointer to an object. Keep these checks
3981 in ascending tree code order. */
3982#define TYPE_PTROB_P(NODE) \
3983 (TYPE_PTR_P (NODE) && TYPE_OBJ_P (TREE_TYPE (NODE)))
3984
3985/* Returns true if NODE is a reference to an object. Keep these checks
3986 in ascending tree code order. */
3987#define TYPE_REF_OBJ_P(NODE) \
3988 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == REFERENCE_TYPE && TYPE_OBJ_P (TREE_TYPE (NODE)))
3989
3990/* Returns true if NODE is a pointer to an object, or a pointer to
3991 void. Keep these checks in ascending tree code order. */
3992#define TYPE_PTROBV_P(NODE) \
3993 (TYPE_PTR_P (NODE) \
3994 && !(TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (NODE)) == FUNCTION_TYPE \
3995 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (NODE)) == METHOD_TYPE))
3996
3997/* Returns true if NODE is a pointer to function type. */
3998#define TYPE_PTRFN_P(NODE) \
3999 (TYPE_PTR_P (NODE) \
4000 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (NODE)) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
4001
4002/* Returns true if NODE is a reference to function type. */
4003#define TYPE_REFFN_P(NODE) \
4004 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == REFERENCE_TYPE \
4005 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (NODE)) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
4006
4007/* Returns true if NODE is a pointer to member function type. */
4008#define TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P(NODE) \
4009 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == RECORD_TYPE \
4010 && TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FLAG (NODE))
4011
4012#define TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FLAG(NODE) \
4013 (TYPE_LANG_FLAG_2 (RECORD_TYPE_CHECK (NODE)))
4014
4015/* Returns true if NODE is a pointer-to-member. */
4016#define TYPE_PTRMEM_P(NODE) \
4017 (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (NODE) || TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (NODE))
4018
4019/* Returns true if NODE is a pointer or a pointer-to-member. */
4020#define TYPE_PTR_OR_PTRMEM_P(NODE) \
4021 (TYPE_PTR_P (NODE) || TYPE_PTRMEM_P (NODE))
4022
4023/* Indicates when overload resolution may resolve to a pointer to
4024 member function. [expr.unary.op]/3 */
4025#define PTRMEM_OK_P(NODE) \
4026 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (TREE_CHECK3 ((NODE), ADDR_EXPR, OFFSET_REF, SCOPE_REF))
4027
4028/* Get the POINTER_TYPE to the METHOD_TYPE associated with this
4029 pointer to member function. TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P _must_ be true,
4030 before using this macro. */
4031#define TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE(NODE) \
4032 (cp_build_qualified_type (TREE_TYPE (TYPE_FIELDS (NODE)),\
4033 cp_type_quals (NODE)))
4034
4035/* As above, but can be used in places that want an lvalue at the expense
4036 of not necessarily having the correct cv-qualifiers. */
4037#define TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE_RAW(NODE) \
4038 (TREE_TYPE (TYPE_FIELDS (NODE)))
4039
4040/* Returns `A' for a type like `int (A::*)(double)' */
4041#define TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_OBJECT_TYPE(NODE) \
4042 TYPE_METHOD_BASETYPE (TREE_TYPE (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (NODE)))
4043
4044/* These are use to manipulate the canonical RECORD_TYPE from the
4045 hashed POINTER_TYPE, and can only be used on the POINTER_TYPE. */
4046#define TYPE_GET_PTRMEMFUNC_TYPE(NODE) \
4047 (TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE) ? LANG_TYPE_PTRMEM_CHECK (NODE)->record : NULL)
4048#define TYPE_SET_PTRMEMFUNC_TYPE(NODE, VALUE) \
4049 do { \
4050 if (TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE) == NULL) \
4051 { \
4052 TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE) \
4053 = (struct lang_type *) ggc_internal_cleared_alloc \
4054 (sizeof (struct lang_type_ptrmem)); \
4055 TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.ptrmem.h.is_lang_type_class = 0; \
4056 } \
4057 TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE)->u.ptrmem.record = (VALUE); \
4058 } while (0)
4059
4060/* For a pointer-to-member type of the form `T X::*', this is `X'.
4061 For a type like `void (X::*)() const', this type is `X', not `const
4062 X'. To get at the `const X' you have to look at the
4063 TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE; there, the first parameter will have
4064 type `const X*'. */
4065#define TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE(NODE) \
4066 (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (NODE) \
4067 ? TYPE_OFFSET_BASETYPE (NODE) \
4068 : TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_OBJECT_TYPE (NODE))
4069
4070/* For a pointer-to-member type of the form `T X::*', this is `T'. */
4071#define TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE(NODE) \
4072 (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (NODE) \
4073 ? TREE_TYPE (NODE) \
4074 : TREE_TYPE (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (NODE)))
4075
4076/* For a pointer-to-member constant `X::Y' this is the RECORD_TYPE for
4077 `X'. */
4078#define PTRMEM_CST_CLASS(NODE) \
4079 TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (PTRMEM_CST_CHECK (NODE)))
4080
4081/* For a pointer-to-member constant `X::Y' this is the _DECL for
4082 `Y'. */
4083#define PTRMEM_CST_MEMBER(NODE) (((ptrmem_cst_t)PTRMEM_CST_CHECK (NODE))->member)
4084
4085/* The expression in question for a TYPEOF_TYPE. */
4086#define TYPEOF_TYPE_EXPR(NODE) (TYPE_VALUES_RAW (TYPEOF_TYPE_CHECK (NODE)))
4087
4088/* The type in question for an UNDERLYING_TYPE. */
4089#define UNDERLYING_TYPE_TYPE(NODE) \
4090 (TYPE_VALUES_RAW (UNDERLYING_TYPE_CHECK (NODE)))
4091
4092/* The type in question for BASES. */
4093#define BASES_TYPE(NODE) \
4094 (TYPE_VALUES_RAW (BASES_CHECK (NODE)))
4095
4096#define BASES_DIRECT(NODE) \
4097 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (BASES_CHECK (NODE))
4098
4099/* The expression in question for a DECLTYPE_TYPE. */
4100#define DECLTYPE_TYPE_EXPR(NODE) (TYPE_VALUES_RAW (DECLTYPE_TYPE_CHECK (NODE)))
4101
4102/* Whether the DECLTYPE_TYPE_EXPR of NODE was originally parsed as an
4103 id-expression or a member-access expression. When false, it was
4104 parsed as a full expression. */
4105#define DECLTYPE_TYPE_ID_EXPR_OR_MEMBER_ACCESS_P(NODE) \
4106 (DECLTYPE_TYPE_CHECK (NODE))->type_common.string_flag
4107
4108/* These flags indicate that we want different semantics from normal
4109 decltype: lambda capture just drops references, init capture
4110 uses auto semantics, lambda proxies look through implicit dereference. */
4111#define DECLTYPE_FOR_LAMBDA_CAPTURE(NODE) \
4112 TREE_LANG_FLAG_0 (DECLTYPE_TYPE_CHECK (NODE))
4113#define DECLTYPE_FOR_INIT_CAPTURE(NODE) \
4114 TREE_LANG_FLAG_1 (DECLTYPE_TYPE_CHECK (NODE))
4115#define DECLTYPE_FOR_LAMBDA_PROXY(NODE) \
4116 TREE_LANG_FLAG_2 (DECLTYPE_TYPE_CHECK (NODE))
4117#define DECLTYPE_FOR_REF_CAPTURE(NODE) \
4118 TREE_LANG_FLAG_3 (DECLTYPE_TYPE_CHECK (NODE))
4119
4120/* Nonzero for VAR_DECL and FUNCTION_DECL node means that `extern' was
4121 specified in its declaration. This can also be set for an
4122 erroneously declared PARM_DECL. */
4123#define DECL_THIS_EXTERN(NODE) \
4124 DECL_LANG_FLAG_2 (VAR_FUNCTION_OR_PARM_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
4125
4126/* Nonzero for VAR_DECL and FUNCTION_DECL node means that `static' was
4127 specified in its declaration. This can also be set for an
4128 erroneously declared PARM_DECL. */
4129#define DECL_THIS_STATIC(NODE) \
4130 DECL_LANG_FLAG_6 (VAR_FUNCTION_OR_PARM_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
4131
4132/* Nonzero for FIELD_DECL node means that this field is a lambda capture
4133 field for an array of runtime bound. */
4134#define DECL_VLA_CAPTURE_P(NODE) \
4135 DECL_LANG_FLAG_1 (FIELD_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
4136
4137/* Nonzero for PARM_DECL node means that this is an array function
4138 parameter, i.e, a[] rather than *a. */
4139#define DECL_ARRAY_PARAMETER_P(NODE) \
4140 DECL_LANG_FLAG_1 (PARM_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
4141
4142/* Nonzero for a FIELD_DECL who's NSMDI is currently being
4143 instantiated. */
4144#define DECL_INSTANTIATING_NSDMI_P(NODE) \
4145 DECL_LANG_FLAG_2 (FIELD_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
4146
4147/* Nonzero for FIELD_DECL node means that this field is a base class
4148 of the parent object, as opposed to a member field. */
4149#define DECL_FIELD_IS_BASE(NODE) \
4150 DECL_LANG_FLAG_6 (FIELD_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
4151
4152/* Nonzero for FIELD_DECL node means that this field is a simple (no
4153 explicit initializer) lambda capture field, making it invisible to
4154 name lookup in unevaluated contexts. */
4155#define DECL_NORMAL_CAPTURE_P(NODE) \
4156 DECL_LANG_FLAG_7 (FIELD_DECL_CHECK (NODE))
4157
4158/* Nonzero if TYPE is an anonymous union or struct type. We have to use a
4159 flag for this because "A union for which objects or pointers are
4160 declared is not an anonymous union" [class.union]. */
4161#define ANON_AGGR_TYPE_P(NODE) \
4162 (CLASS_TYPE_P (NODE) && LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->anon_aggr)
4163#define SET_ANON_AGGR_TYPE_P(NODE) \
4164 (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->anon_aggr = 1)
4165
4166/* Nonzero if TYPE is an anonymous union type. */
4167#define ANON_UNION_TYPE_P(NODE) \
4168 (TREE_CODE (NODE) == UNION_TYPE && ANON_AGGR_TYPE_P (NODE))
4169
4170/* Define fields and accessors for nodes representing declared names. */

4172/* Nonzero if TYPE is an unnamed class with a typedef for linkage purposes. */
4173#define TYPE_WAS_UNNAMED(NODE) (LANG_TYPE_CLASS_CHECK (NODE)->was_anonymous)
